    "log_text": "---\njob_id: f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243\nchat_id: 01N7P0NP2EPB8EXEDTWD\ngenerated_at: 2026-07-07T19:50:21.397494\nsource: NOVA\npartial_response: False\n---\n\nI now have all the data needed to compile the comprehensive RCA report. I also noticed a critical note in the resource description for `crm-ubuntu232`: **\"syelugub- 7/31 space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"** \u2014 confirming a known prior space issue on this host. Let me now compile the full RCA report.\n\n---\n\n# CloudBees CD/RO \u2014 Root Cause Analysis Report\n\n---\n\n## # 1 Summary\n\nJob `CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2_20260706_021954_022000` (Job ID: `f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243`) failed on **2026-07-06** at **09:44:05 UTC** due to the `BBS_PackMake` step exiting with **exit code 125** on agent host **crm-ubuntu232**. The CloudBees `errorHandling=abortJob` policy on that step triggered an immediate job abort.\n\nThe `BuildInfoJson` property explicitly records `failedReason=PostPackBBS`, confirming the failure occurred during the **post-pack BBS phase** of the build. Exit code 125 in a Docker-based build context indicates the **Docker container failed to run or be created** \u2014 not a failure of the container's internal process. This is consistent with a resource-level failure on the agent host.\n\nDatadog telemetry on `crm-ubuntu232` shows **memory utilization rising from ~74% to ~85%** (~42 GB increase) over the job window, with **elevated kernel/system CPU** (cpu_sys exceeding cpu_user during 09:28\u201309:39), indicating heavy I/O or syscall pressure. The agent's CMDB resource description contains a historical annotation: **\"syelugub- 7/31 space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"**, confirming this host has a documented prior disk space problem. A concurrent job (`f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243`) was also running on the same agent at the time of failure.\n\nThe most probable root cause is a **build-time failure within the BBS_PackMake/PostPackBBS phase**, most likely caused by a Docker container creation failure (exit code 125) potentially driven by resource pressure (memory growth, I/O contention) or a Docker-level error on the agent. Direct step execution logs on `crm-ubuntu232` are required to confirm the exact sub-cause.\n\n---\n\n## # 2 Job Context\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Job ID** | `f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243` |\n| **Job Name** | `CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2_20260706_021954_022000` |\n| **Project** | `CRMBuilds` |\n| **Procedure** | `Build.Container.Rel.602829` |\n| **Launched By** | `tiberiumUserEC10_11` |\n| **Run As** | `aswbldsv` |\n| **Execution Node (Agent)** | `crm-ubuntu232` (ID: `f0ec3f7a-9c3e-f110-ad8b-2686f9881e6f`) |\n| **Build Resource Pool** | `CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu20-04` |\n| **Workspace (Unix)** | `/prj/qct/asw/ecmdr_ws_crm/BOOT.XF.4.1.4-00067-KAMORTALAZ-1_20260706_024225_024238` |\n| **CWD** | `/local/mnt/workspace/CRMBuilds/BOOT.XF.4.1.4-00067-KAMORTALAZ-1_20260706_024225` |\n| **Start** | `2026-07-06T09:20:00.467Z` |\n| **Finish** | `2026-07-06T09:46:56.009Z` |\n| **Elapsed** | ~26 min 56 sec (1,603,118 ms) |\n| **Final Status** | `completed` |\n| **Outcome** | `error` |\n| **Abort Status** | `ABORT` |\n| **Environment** | Production (`Prod`) |\n| **DB Host** | `Oil` |\n| **Commander Endpoint** | `qso-bicmdr.qualcomm.com` |\n| **Client** | `KALPENIAAAAANAZT` |\n| **Software Image** | `TZ.XF.5.25` |\n| **Image Revision** | `179`, Spin `2` |\n| **Site** | `SanDiego` |\n| **Workflow Type** | `ONPREMCONTAINERIZED` |\n| **Host OS** | `Ubuntu20_04` |\n| **Build Command** | `python3 trustzone_images/build/ms/build_all.py CHIPSET=kalpeni SIGNSERVER=https://crm-sign SIGNTYPE=CASS SIGNPORT=50110` |\n| **Build Path** | `\\\\snowcone\\builds674\\PROD\\CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2` |\n| **Linux Build Path** | `/prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds674/PROD/CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2` |\n| **Built By** | `ravind` |\n| **Ref Build** | `TZ.XF.5.25-00179-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2` |\n| **DCE Config** | `Config.DCE.Prod` |\n\n---\n\n## # 3 Build Timeline\n\nAll times UTC.\n\n| Time (UTC) | Event |\n|---|---|\n| `09:20:00.467` | Job created and started \u2014 `CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2` |\n| `09:20:00` \u2013 `09:43:34` | Sequential steps executed: `InitCredentialsAndServer` \u2192 `Init` \u2192 `Docker Login` \u2192 `GetQTI` \u2192 `GetBCI` \u2192 `GetParameterStore` \u2192 `Setup` \u2192 `BBS_sync` \u2192 `Sync` \u2192 `sync_spacer` \u2192 `PostSync` \u2192 `BBS_strip` |\n| `09:21:00` \u2013 `09:28:00` | Agent CPU low (0.11\u20130.39%), memory at ~74% (~186.8 GB used) |\n| `09:25:00` \u2013 `09:32:00` | CPU system spikes sharply \u2014 cpu_sys peaks at avg 12.60%, max 14.35%; cpu_sys exceeds cpu_user (heavy kernel/I/O activity) |\n| `09:28:00` \u2013 `09:30:00` | CPU user peaks at avg 8.10%, max 14.37% |\n| `09:43:34.761` | `BBS_PackMake` step transitions: `pending \u2192 runnable` |\n| `09:43:34.857` | Resource `crm-ubuntu232` assigned to `BBS_PackMake` by scheduler `las-colo12-j13-10` |\n| `09:43:34.861` | `BBS_PackMake` transitions: `runnable \u2192 scheduled` |\n| `09:43:34.934` | `BBS_PackMake` invoked on `crm-ubuntu232` by `las-colo12-j13-11` |\n| `09:43:34.974` | `BBS_PackMake` transitions: `scheduled \u2192 running` |\n| `09:44:00` | Memory on `crm-ubuntu232` reaches ~85% (~228\u2013229 GB used); ~42 GB increase since job start |\n| `09:44:05.422` | `FinishCommandOperation` records exit code **125** for `BBS_PackMake` |\n| `09:44:05.430` | `RunCommandCallback` confirms exit code **125** |\n| `09:44:05.441` | `CommitCommandResultsOperation` transitions step from `success \u2192 error` |\n| `09:44:05.440` | Resource `crm-ubuntu232` released from `BBS_PackMake` (step duration: ~30 seconds) |\n| `09:44:05.483` | `CheckAbortCondition` evaluates: `errorHandling=abortJob` \u2192 triggers abort |\n| `09:44:05.512` | Job `modifyTime` updated \u2014 status: `running_error` |\n| `09:44:05.517` | `AbortJobOperation` triggered on `las-colo12-j13-11` |\n| `09:44:07` | `FixBuildStatus` step (alwaysRun) completes with status=0 |\n| `09:44:08` | `Finalize` step (alwaysRun, parallel) invoked |\n| `09:46:42.241` | `BuildInfoJson` property written \u2014 `failedReason=PostPackBBS`, `buildStatus=Failed` |\n| `09:46:45.105` | `PostTimingsToSplunk` step completes successfully |\n| `09:46:48.922` | Non-fatal `NoSuchProperty` for `customType` on `las-colo12-j13-10` (irrelevant to failure) |\n| `09:46:56.009` | Job finalized \u2014 outcome: `error`, abortStatus: `ABORT` |\n\n---\n\n## # 4 Execution Path Inventory\n\n### Failed Step\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Step Name** | `BBS_PackMake` |\n| **Step ID** | `f1791bdd-17fb-f111-93af-4efb9ff91010` |\n| **Exit Code** | **125** |\n| **Step Status** | `error` |\n| **Error Handling** | `abortJob` |\n| **Parallel** | Yes |\n| **Step Timeout** | `2026-07-06T03:13:34.907` (not reached \u2014 failure was not timeout-related) |\n| **Step Start** | `2026-07-06T09:43:34.974Z` |\n| **Step End** | `2026-07-06T09:44:05.441Z` |\n| **Step Duration** | ~30 seconds |\n| **Failed Reason (BuildInfoJson)** | `PostPackBBS` |\n\n### Agent Host\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Hostname** | `crm-ubuntu232` |\n| **Agent ID** | `f0ec3f7a-9c3e-f110-ad8b-2686f9881e6f` |\n| **OS** | Linux Ubuntu 20.04 (`5.4.0-107-generic #121-Ubuntu SMP`) |\n| **Architecture** | `x86_64` |\n| **Agent Version** | `2024.12.0.177508` |\n| **Protocol** | `6` |\n| **Agent State** | `alive` |\n| **Zone** | `default` (TRANSIENT) |\n| **Step Limit** | 9 |\n| **Step Count at Failure** | 2 (concurrent job also running) |\n| **Hardware** | HP BL460c Gen9 |\n| **Known Issue** | Resource description: *\"syelugub- 7/31 space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"* |\n\n### Concurrent Job on Same Agent\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Job ID** | `f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243` |\n| **Steps Running** | `VerifySrc`, `Make` (both status=0) |\n| **Impact** | Contributed to memory growth and I/O pressure on `crm-ubuntu232` during `BBS_PackMake` execution |\n\n### Commander Nodes\n\n| Node | IP | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `las-colo12-j13-09` | `10.81.104.241` | API handler, state machine |\n| `las-colo12-j13-10` | `10.81.104.242` | Scheduler / resource assignment |\n| `las-colo12-j13-11` | (not recorded) | State machine / dispatch / abort |\n| `qso-bicmdr.qualcomm.com` | \u2014 | Commander public endpoint |\n\n**Commander Assessment:** Commander nodes operated normally. Scheduling, invocation, abort, and finalization all completed without error. Commander is **NOT** a contributing factor.\n\n### Invoked Services (Directly Referenced)\n\n| Service | Evidence |\n|---|---|\n| **Sign Server** | `https://crm-sign` (SIGNSERVER in build command) \u2014 used by `BBS_PackMake` |\n| **Build Storage** | `\\\\snowcone\\builds674\\PROD` / `/prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds674/PROD` |\n| **Workspace NFS** | `\\\\snowcone\\ecmdr_ws_crm\\...` / `/prj/qct/asw/ecmdr_ws_crm/...` |\n| **Docker** | Workflow type `ONPREMCONTAINERIZED`; exit code 125 = Docker container creation failure |\n| **CASS Sign Service** | `SIGNTYPE=CASS SIGNPORT=50110` |\n\n---\n\n## # 5 Detected Error Codes\n\n| Code | Location | Meaning | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Exit Code 125** | `BBS_PackMake` step on `crm-ubuntu232` | In Docker context: **container failed to run or be created** (Docker daemon error, not the container's own exit code). Exit code 125 is returned by `docker run` when the container cannot be started. | `FinishCommandOperation` at `09:44:05.422`, `RunCommandCallback` at `09:44:05.430`, `CommitCommandResultsOperation` at `09:44:05.441` \u2014 all from Splunk `index=ecommander` |\n| **failedReason=PostPackBBS** | `BuildInfoJson` property | Failure occurred specifically in the **PostPackBBS** sub-phase of the BBS_PackMake step | `BuildInfoJson` written at `09:46:42.241Z` \u2014 Splunk `index=ecommander` |\n| **ABORT** | Job-level abort status | `errorHandling=abortJob` on `BBS_PackMake` triggered job abort | `CheckAbortCondition` at `09:44:05.483`, `AbortJobOperation` at `09:44:05.517` \u2014 Splunk `index=ecommander` |\n| **NoSuchProperty (customType)** | `las-colo12-j13-10` at `09:46:48.922` | Non-fatal property lookup during job finalization | Splunk `index=ecommander` \u2014 **NOT related to failure** |\n| **NoSuchProperty (report-urls)** | `las-colo12-j13-09` | Non-fatal property lookup | Splunk `index=ecommander` \u2014 **NOT related to failure** |\n\n---\n\n## # 6 Correlated Observations\n\n### CloudBees\n\n- **Job abort message:** `\"Job error [Aborted]: step 'BBS_PackMake' failed and its error handling aborted the job.\"` \u2014 confirmed in Splunk `index=ecommander`.\n- **Exit code 125** confirmed by three independent CloudBees Commander log events: `FinishCommandOperation`, `RunCommandCallback`, `CommitCommandResultsOperation`.\n- **failedReason=PostPackBBS** in `BuildInfoJson` confirms the failure sub-phase.\n- **Step duration was ~30 seconds** \u2014 extremely short for a PackMake step, consistent with a container startup failure rather than a compile or link failure.\n- **Timeout was NOT the cause** \u2014 the `Check If Any Step Failed due to Time Out` step completed with `errorHandling=ignore`, confirming the abort was triggered by the exit code, not a timeout.\n- **Concurrent job** `f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243` was running `VerifySrc` and `Make` steps on the same agent simultaneously, consuming additional CPU, memory, and I/O resources.\n- **alwaysRun steps** (`FixBuildStatus`, `Finalize`, `PostTimingsToSplunk`) all completed successfully post-abort, confirming the Commander infrastructure was healthy.\n\n### Agent Host (`crm-ubuntu232`)\n\n**Source: Datadog Metrics \u2014 Correlation Window: `09:20:00Z` \u2013 `09:44:05Z`**\n\n| Metric | Observation | Assessment |\n|---|---|---|\n| **CPU User** | Peaked avg 8.10% at 09:28\u201309:30, max 14.37%; elevated 4.9\u20137.7% through 09:44 | Moderate \u2014 not exhausted |\n| **CPU System** | Peaked avg 12.60% at 09:30\u201309:32, max 14.35%; **cpu_sys > cpu_user** during 09:28\u201309:39 | **Significant** \u2014 indicates heavy kernel activity (I/O wait, syscalls, context switching) |\n| **Memory Used** | Rose from ~186.8 GB (~74%) at 09:00 to ~228\u2013229 GB (~85%) by 09:44 \u2014 **~42 GB increase** | **Significant** \u2014 sustained memory growth with no release; concurrent job contributing |\n| **Memory Total** | Fixed at ~251.7 GB | No OOM observed, but headroom reduced to ~22\u201323 GB |\n| **Disk `/local/mnt`** | Gradual increase from ~12.9% to ~15.8%; free space declined ~31 GB (919 GB \u2192 888 GB) over 47 min | Moderate \u2014 not full, but declining |\n| **Disk `/` (root FS)** | Stable ~52.5% | Normal |\n| **Disk `/var`** | Stable ~26.9%, slight drop to ~25.1% near end | Normal |\n| **Snap mounts** | 100% \u2014 all read-only loop mounts | Normal (expected) |\n\n**Known Historical Issue:** The CloudBees resource description for `crm-ubuntu232` contains: *\"syelugub- 7/31 space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"* \u2014 confirming this host has a documented prior disk space problem and was previously taken out of service for it.\n\n**Datadog Logs:** No logs found for `crm-ubuntu232` in the Datadog flex tier for the failure window. Step execution logs must be examined directly on the agent.\n\n**SCOM:** No active SCOM alerts for `crm-ubuntu232`.\n\n### Commander Host\n\n- `las-colo12-j13-09`: API thread CPU 77% during `findJobSteps` (155ms), 45% during `getJobDetails` (109ms) \u2014 brief, non-fatal, normal API load.\n- `las-colo12-j13-10`: Scheduler operating normally; resource assignment and scheduling completed without error.\n- `las-colo12-j13-11`: State machine, dispatch, and abort operations completed normally.\n- **No Commander-level errors contributed to the failure.**\n\n### Datadog\n\n- No Datadog alerts referencing Job ID `f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243`, build name, or agent host `crm-ubuntu232` were found.\n- Datadog metrics on `crm-ubuntu232` show memory pressure and elevated kernel CPU \u2014 directly relevant to the agent host.\n- No findings from Datadog are excluded as out-of-scope.\n\n### Splunk\n\n- `index=ecommander` provided all primary evidence: job metadata, step sequence, exit code, abort chain, BuildInfoJson, agent identity, concurrent job, and Commander node activity.\n- All findings are directly traceable to the failed job and agent.\n\n### External Dependency\n\n| Service | Assessment |\n|---|---|\n| **Sign Server (`https://crm-sign`, CASS port 50110)** | No evidence of sign server failure in available data. Step failed in ~30 seconds \u2014 insufficient time to complete a signing operation. Cannot confirm or exclude sign server involvement without step logs. |\n| **Build Storage (`snowcone/builds674`)** | No storage failure events found. `/local/mnt` disk declining but not full. Cannot confirm or exclude without step logs. |\n| **Docker Daemon on `crm-ubuntu232`** | Exit code 125 is the canonical Docker \"container failed to run/create\" code. Docker daemon state on the agent at failure time is unknown without step logs. Memory pressure (~85% used) could cause Docker container creation failures. |\n\n---\n\n## # 7 Probable Root Cause\n\n**Primary Root Cause: Docker Container Creation Failure (Exit Code 125) During PostPackBBS Phase**\n\n**Evidence Chain:**\n\n1. `BBS_PackMake` step exited with **exit code 125** \u2014 confirmed by three independent CloudBees Commander log events (`FinishCommandOperation`, `RunCommandCallback`, `CommitCommandResultsOperation`) at `09:44:05Z`.\n2. Exit code 125 in a Docker-based workflow (`ONPREMCONTAINERIZED`) means **`docker run` failed to create or start the container** \u2014 this is a Docker daemon-level error, not a build code error.\n3. `BuildInfoJson.failedReason=PostPackBBS` confirms the failure occurred in the **PostPackBBS sub-phase** of the step.\n4. Step duration was **~30 seconds** \u2014 far too short for a TrustZone firmware pack/make operation to complete or fail on code; consistent with a container startup failure.\n5. Agent `crm-ubuntu232` had **memory utilization at ~85%** (~228 GB of 251 GB used) at the time of failure, with a **~42 GB increase** over the job window driven by both this job and a concurrent job (`f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243`).\n6. **Elevated kernel CPU** (cpu_sys > cpu_user during 09:28\u201309:39) indicates heavy I/O or syscall pressure on the agent, consistent with Docker image layer operations or filesystem pressure.\n7. The agent has a **documented prior disk space issue** (resource description: *\"syelugub- 7/31 space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"*), indicating this host has a history of resource-related failures.\n8. **Direct step execution logs on `crm-ubuntu232`** for the `BBS_PackMake` step are not available in Splunk or Datadog \u2014 the exact Docker error message (e.g., \"no space left on device\", \"cannot allocate memory\", \"image pull failed\") cannot be determined without examining the step log file directly.\n\n**Most Likely Sub-Cause (requires log confirmation):**\nDocker container creation failed due to one of:\n- Insufficient memory to allocate the container (memory at 85%, concurrent job consuming resources)\n- Docker image layer extraction failure due to disk pressure on `/local/mnt` (declining free space)\n- Docker daemon error triggered by I/O contention (elevated kernel CPU)\n\n---\n\n## # 8 Confidence Level\n\n### **MEDIUM**\n\n**Reason:**\n\n- **HIGH confidence** elements: Job ID, step name, exit code 125, failedReason=PostPackBBS, abort chain, agent identity, step duration \u2014 all directly confirmed by Splunk `index=ecommander`.\n- **MEDIUM confidence** elements: The link between memory/I/O pressure and the Docker exit code 125 is strongly correlated but not directly proven \u2014 the step execution log on `crm-ubuntu232` was not available in Splunk or Datadog.\n- **Cannot achieve HIGH confidence** without the `BBS_PackMake` step log file (`BBS_PackMake.f1791bdd-17fb-f111-93af-4efb9ff91010.log`) from `crm-ubuntu232`, which would contain the exact Docker error message.\n- No speculation has been introduced. The root cause is bounded by available evidence.\n\n---\n\n## # 9 Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\n\n| Assessment | Result |\n|---|---|\n| **Infrastructure Issue** | **YES** |\n| **Code Issue** | **NO** |\n| **Mixed** | **NO** |\n\n**Reason:**\n\nExit code 125 is a **Docker daemon / container runtime error**, not a compiler, linker, or build script error. The step failed in ~30 seconds \u2014 insufficient time for a build code failure. The failure occurred at the container creation level (PostPackBBS phase), before the build command (`python3 trustzone_images/build/ms/build_all.py`) could execute or fail. Memory pressure (~85% utilization) and elevated kernel CPU on `crm-ubuntu232` are consistent with an infrastructure-level resource constraint causing Docker container creation to fail. The agent has a documented prior history of resource-related failures.\n\n---\n\n## # 10 Recommended Remediation\n\n1. **Retrieve and examine the BBS_PackMake step log immediately:**\n   - File: `BBS_PackMake.f1791bdd-17fb-f111-93af-4efb9ff91010.log` on `crm-ubuntu232`\n   - Path: `/local/mnt/workspace/CRMBuilds/` or the workspace directory\n   - This log will contain the exact Docker error message confirming the sub-cause.\n\n2. **Investigate Docker daemon state on `crm-ubuntu232` at failure time:**\n   - Check `/var/log/syslog` and `journalctl -u docker` on `crm-ubuntu232` around `09:43:34Z \u2013 09:44:05Z`.\n   - Look for OOM killer events, Docker daemon errors, or storage driver errors.\n\n3. **Address memory pressure on `crm-ubuntu232`:**\n   - At failure time, memory was at ~85% (~228 GB of 251 GB). With a concurrent job also running, available headroom was ~22\u201323 GB.\n   - Review the step limit (currently 9) and consider reducing concurrent step assignments to this agent.\n   - Investigate whether the concurrent job `f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243` should be scheduled on a different agent.\n\n4. **Investigate the `/local/mnt` disk trend:**\n   - Free space declined ~31 GB over 47 minutes. While not full at failure time, this trend warrants monitoring.\n   - Check Docker image cache size on `/local/mnt` \u2014 stale images may be consuming space.\n   - Run `docker system prune` on `crm-ubuntu232` to reclaim disk space.\n\n5. **Retry the failed job** after confirming agent resource health.\n\n---\n\n## # 11 Preventive Actions\n\n1. **Implement memory utilization alerting on CRM build agents:**\n   - Alert threshold: >80% memory utilization sustained for >5 minutes on `CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu20-04` pool agents.\n   - This would have flagged `crm-ubuntu232` before the failure.\n\n2. **Implement disk space alerting on `/local/mnt`:**\n   - Alert threshold: <200 GB free on `/local/mnt` (currently declining).\n   - Given the documented prior space issue on `crm-ubuntu232`, this is a known risk.\n\n3. **Implement Docker health checks as a pre-step:**\n   - Add a lightweight pre-flight step before `BBS_PackMake` to verify Docker daemon health and available disk/memory.\n\n4. **Review concurrent step scheduling policy for `crm-ubuntu232`:**\n   - The agent ran 2 concurrent jobs at the time of failure. Consider reducing `stepLimit` or implementing resource-aware scheduling to prevent memory contention.\n\n5. **Establish a regular Docker image cache cleanup schedule on all CRM build agents:**\n   - Scheduled `docker system prune -f` to prevent disk accumulation on `/local/mnt`.\n\n6. **Document and track the `crm-ubuntu232` resource history:**\n   - The existing annotation (*\"space issue 7/17 smanley - put back in service\"*) indicates this host has recurring resource issues. Consider a formal health review before returning it to the production pool.\n\n---\n\n## # 12 Sources Used\n\n| # | Source Type | Query Window | Evidence | Relevance |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | **Splunk** `index=ecommander` | `-7d` to `now` | Job ID, Job Name, Project, Procedure, Owner, Start/Finish times, Outcome, Abort status, error message | Primary job identity and metadata |\n| 2 | **Splunk** `index=ecommander` | `-7d` to `now` | Exit code 125 (FinishCommandOperation, RunCommandCallback, CommitCommandResultsOperation), abort chain, BuildInfoJson (failedReason=PostPackBBS), step sequence, agent assignment | Primary failure evidence \u2014 exit code and abort chain |\n| 3 | **Splunk** `index=ecommander` | `-7d` to `now` | Agent `crm-ubuntu232` identity, OS, agent version, zone, stepCount/stepLimit, concurrent job `f1791f06-4a84-f1fa-9190-1ea035bf3243`, resource description with prior space issue annotation | Agent host identification and concurrent job evidence |\n| 4 | **Splunk** `index=ecommander` | `-7d` to `now` | Commander nodes `las-colo12-j13-09/10/11`, API thread CPU, scheduling events, LDAP lookup, web host activity | Commander node health assessment |\n| 5 | **Datadog Metrics** (`system.cpu.user`, `system.cpu.system`) | `09:00:00Z \u2013 09:47:00Z` | CPU user peaked 8.10% avg / 14.37% max; cpu_sys peaked 12.60% avg / 14.35% max; cpu_sys > cpu_user during 09:28\u201309:39 | Agent host CPU and kernel activity during job execution |\n| 6 | **Datadog Metrics** (`system.mem.used`, `system.mem.total`) | `09:00:00Z \u2013 09:47:00Z` | Memory rose from ~186.8 GB (74%) to ~228\u2013229 GB (85%); ~42 GB increase; no OOM | Agent host memory pressure during job execution |\n| 7 | **Datadog Metrics** (`system.disk.in_use`, `system.disk.free`) | `09:00:00Z \u2013 09:47:00Z` | `/local/mnt` declined ~31 GB (919\u2192888 GB free); root FS stable at 52.5%; snap mounts at 100% (normal for read-only loop mounts) | Agent host disk utilization during job execution |\n| 8 | **Datadog Logs** | `09:43:00Z \u2013 09:44:30Z` | **0 results** \u2014 no Datadog logs for `crm-ubuntu232` in flex tier | Confirmed: no Datadog log coverage for agent host |\n| 9 | **SCOM** | Current | **0 active alerts** for `crm-ubuntu232` | Confirmed: no active SCOM alerts on agent host |\n\n---\n\n> **\u26a0\ufe0f Data Gap Notice:**\n> The `BBS_PackMake` step execution log file (`BBS_PackMake.f1791bdd-17fb-f111-93af-4efb9ff91010.log`) on agent host `crm-ubuntu232` was **not available** in Splunk or Datadog. This log contains the exact Docker error message that would confirm the precise sub-cause of the exit code 125 failure. **CloudBees step execution logs must be examined directly on `crm-ubuntu232`** to elevate confidence from MEDIUM to HIGH and confirm whether the failure was caused by memory exhaustion, disk pressure, Docker image pull failure, or another Docker daemon error.\n",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_rca_f1791bdd\",\"name\":\"RCA_f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243.txt\",\"description\":\"Source RCA log for job_id f1791bdd-0bec-f151-8192-1ea035bf3243, chat_id 01N7P0NP2EPB8EXEDTWD, generated_at 2026-07-07T19:50:21.397494, source NOVA, partial_response False.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"proc_build_container_rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Container.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees CD/RO procedure for job CI_TZ.XF.5.25-00179.2-KALPENIAAAAANAZT-2_20260706_021954_022000 in project CRMBuilds. The job ran in production on agent crm-ubuntu232 and ended with outcome error and abortStatus ABORT.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_bbs_packmake\",\"name\":\"BBS_PackMake\",\"description\":\"Failed CloudBees step f1791bdd-17fb-f111-93af-4efb9ff91010. It ran on crm-ubuntu232 from 2026-07-06T09:43:34.974Z to 2026-07-06T09:44:05.441Z, lasted about 30 seconds, exited with code 125, transitioned to error, and had errorHandling=abortJob.\"},{\"id\":\"step_fix_build_status\",\"name\":\"FixBuildStatus\",\"description\":\"Post-abort alwaysRun step that completed successfully with status 0 at about 2026-07-06T09:44:07Z.\"},{\"id\":\"step_finalize\",\"name\":\"Finalize\",\"description\":\"Post-abort alwaysRun parallel step invoked at about 2026-07-06T09:44:08Z.\"},{\"id\":\"step_post_timings_to_splunk\",\"name\":\"PostTimingsToSplunk\",\"description\":\"Post-abort step that completed successfully at 2026-07-06T09:46:45.105Z.\"},{\"id\":\"step_prior_sequence\",\"name\":\"Preceding build steps\",\"description\":\"Sequential steps completed before BBS_PackMake included InitCredentialsAndServer, Init, Docker Login, GetQTI, GetBCI, GetParameterStore, Setup, BBS_sync, Sync, sync_spacer, PostSync, and BBS_strip between about 09:20:00Z and 09:43:34Z.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_failed_packmake\",\"name\":\"Failed PackMake/PostPackBBS step\",\"description\":\"Step classification for BBS_PackMake failure in the PostPackBBS phase, ba