    "file_name": "RCA_f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010.txt",
    "log_text": "Build ID: f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010\n---\n1. Executive Summary\nThe CloudBees CI build CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70 failed on 2026-07-07 due to a Compile Failure in the Make step. The Make step executed on agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07 and exited with an error, triggering an abortJob error-handling policy. This cascaded into a SaveBuild step failure and the cancellation of all downstream packaging and post-processing steps. The agent host showed no resource exhaustion (CPU, memory, disk all healthy). The root cause is a source code or build script compile error within the buildex.py-driven UEFI firmware build for the AthertonPkg target (variants LAA/LAB, Ubuntu 16.04).\n\n---\n2. Job Context\nJob ID: f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010\nJob Name: CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70_20260707_020049_020056\nBuild ID: CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70\nProject: CRMBuilds\nProcedure: Build.Rel.602829\nOutcome: error | abortStatus: ABORT\nFailed Step: Make (primary), SaveBuild (cascading)\nLaunched By: tiberiumUserEC10_11 | Requester: pawkuma\nSoftware Image: BOOT.XF.4.3 | Branch Revision: 00263 | Spin: 70\nTarget: AthertonPkg \u2014 Variants LAA, LAB | OS: Ubuntu 16.04\nBuild Location: \\\\snowcone\\builds677\\PROD\nBuild Delete Date: 2026-07-10\nfailedReason (BuildInfoJson): Compile\n---\n3. Build Timeline\nTime (UTC)\tEvent\tHost\tOutcome\n2026-07-07 09:00:56Z\tJob Created / Started\tlas-colo12-j13-11\tRunning\n2026-07-07 09:00:57Z\tStep: Setup \u2014 Started\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07\tRunning\n2026-07-07 09:01:19Z\tStep: Setup \u2014 Completed\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07\t\u2705 Success (22s)\n2026-07-07 09:02:58Z\tStep: Make \u2014 Submitted\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07\tRunning\n2026-07-07 09:05:29Z\tStep: Make \u2014 FAILED \u2192 abortJob triggered\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07\t\u274c Error (~2m31s)\n2026-07-07 09:05:30Z\tStep: SaveBuild \u2014 Submitted\t\u2014\tRunning\n2026-07-07 09:06:13Z\tStep: SaveBuild \u2014 FAILED\t\u2014\t\u274c Error (~43s)\n2026-07-07 09:06:13Z+\tCascading Cancellations: PreSave, PostSave, ConcurrentCopyPack, PackIt, NonParallelPack, HybridPackIt, HoldLinuxResource, NonParallelPackMake, ConcurrentCopyPackMake, PackMake, CheckAbortCondition\t\u2014\t\ud83d\udeab Canceled\n2026-07-07 09:08:30Z\tStep: PostTimingsToSplunk (alwaysRun) \u2014 Started\tlas-colo12-j13-11\tRunning\n2026-07-07 09:08:39Z\tBuildInfoJson written: status=Failed, failedReason=Compile\tlas-colo12-j13-10\t\u2705 Success\n2026-07-07 09:08:46Z\tStep: PostTimingsToSplunk \u2014 Completed\tlas-colo12-j13-11\t\u2705 Success\n2026-07-07 09:08:49Z\tJob Completed\tlas-colo12-j13-11\t\u274c completed_error / ABORT\n2026-07-07 09:08:56Z\tJob record last modified\t\u2014\tFinal state persisted\nTotal Elapsed Time: ~472 seconds (~7 min 52 sec)\n\n---\n4. Execution Path Inventory\nPrimary Failed Step: Make\nCascading Failed Step: SaveBuild\nAgent Host (Build Server): san-w175-ha1-4-07 (SanDiego site, Ubuntu 16.04)\nBuild Server Drive: G:\nCommander Nodes: las-colo12-j13-09, las-colo12-j13-10, las-colo12-j13-11\nResource Pool: CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu16-04\nWorkspace: crm_ws_sd\nBuild Script: boot_images/QcomPkg/buildex.py (Python 3.8.2)\nBuild Targets: AthertonPkg, QcomToolsPkg, QcomTestPkg, QcomSocPlatTestPkg, QcomCatePkg\nArtifact Store: \\\\snowcone\\builds677\\PROD (Filer)\nDB Host: oil.qualcomm.com (aswproductiondatabase)\nExternal Services Referenced in Setup: pcm.qualcomm.com, csds.qualcomm.com, verifysrc.qualcomm.com, apigw-op.qualcomm.com, license-pdlm-1-encnaa.qualcomm.com (ARM license)\n---\n5. Detected Error Codes & Messages\nSource\tError / Code\tEvidence\nCloudBees Job\tabortStatus: ABORT\terrorMessage: \"step 'Make' failed and its error handling aborted the job\"\nCloudBees Job\toutcome: error\tcombinedStatus: completed_error\nBuildInfoJson\tfailedReason: Compile\tstatus: \"Failed\", serviceType: \"Continuous Integration\"\nCloudBees Job\tSaveBuild also failed\terrorMessage: \"step 'SaveBuild' failed and its error handling aborted the job\"\nCloudBees Step\tSetup exitCode: 0\tSetup completed successfully \u2014 no pre-build environment issue\nNote: Specific compiler error messages (e.g., GCC/LLVM error lines) are in the Make step log file: Make.<stepId>.log on the agent. These were not directly accessible via Splunk telemetry.\n\n---\n6. Correlated Observations\n\u2601\ufe0f CloudBees\nJob metadata explicitly records failedReason: Compile in BuildInfoJson \u2014 this is set programmatically by the build framework after analyzing Make step output.\nMake step ran for ~2 min 31 sec before failing \u2014 consistent with a partial compile that encountered an error mid-build.\nSaveBuild failure is a direct cascade from Make failure \u2014 SaveBuild cannot succeed without valid build artifacts.\nAll 11 downstream steps (PackIt, ConcurrentCopyPack, etc.) were canceled, not failed \u2014 confirming they never executed.\nPost-run alwaysRun steps (Check If Any Step Failed due to TimeOut, Calculate metrics, GetBuildInfo, PostTimingsToSplunk) all completed successfully \u2014 confirming the Commander infrastructure was healthy.\nSetup step succeeded (exitCode: 0, 22s) \u2014 environment setup, DB connectivity, license server, and external service URLs were all reachable.\n\ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Agent Host: san-w175-ha1-4-07\nCPU: Overall utilization was very low (~1.16% user, 98.6% idle) at the time of monitoring. No CPU saturation. \u2705\nMemory: Total 385,619 MB; only ~1.3\u20131.7% used (4,918\u20136,623 MB). No memory pressure. \u2705\nSwap: 0.1\u20130.2% \u2014 negligible. \u2705\nDisk (/local/mnt): 1.7T total, 48 GB used (3%) \u2014 ample space for build workspace. \u2705\n/usr/vice/cache: 72% used (1.1G/1.5G) \u2014 elevated but not full. \u26a0\ufe0f Monitor this.\nLoad Average: Spikes observed at 04:53 PDT (8.09) and 04:13 PDT (5.36) \u2014 these occurred ~4 hours before the build and are OUT_OF_SCOPE.\nPage-out spikes: At 05:33 and 06:13 PDT \u2014 also prior to the build window. OUT_OF_SCOPE.\nSCOM Alerts: No active SCOM alerts on san-w175-ha1-4-07. \u2705\nOther jobs on same agent: No concurrent jobs found on san-w175-ha1-4-07 during the build window in available telemetry.\n\ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Commander Nodes\nlas-colo12-j13-09, las-colo12-j13-10, las-colo12-j13-11: All three nodes participated in job orchestration. All post-run steps completed with exit code 0. No SCOM alerts on any Commander node. Commander infrastructure was healthy. \u2705\nMemory on las-colo12-j13-09: 515,546 MB total, 18.2% used (~94 GB) \u2014 healthy. \u2705\nDisk on las-colo12-j13-09: / at 30%, /var at 35%, /local/mnt at 2% (219G/14T), /usr/vice/cache at 77% \u2014 no critical disk pressure. \u2705\n\ud83d\udcca Datadog\nNo Datadog queries were executed as no direct evidence linked Datadog alerts to this job ID, agent host, or Commander hosts. OUT_OF_SCOPE per RCA scope rules.\n\n\ud83d\udccb Splunk\necommander index confirmed job metadata, step sequence, BuildInfoJson, and error messages.\nos/osetx index confirmed agent host (san-w175-ha1-4-07) and Commander node (las-colo12-j13-09) resource health.\nNo OS-level errors, OOM events, or disk-full conditions found during the build window.\n\ud83d\udd17 External Dependencies\nSetup step succeeded \u2014 confirming the following were reachable at job start:\noil.qualcomm.com (CRM DB)\npcm.qualcomm.com (PCM WebService)\ncsds.qualcomm.com (Software Revision Service)\nverifysrc.qualcomm.com\napigw-op.qualcomm.com (Axway API Gateway)\nlicense-pdlm-1-encnaa.qualcomm.com (ARM License Server)\nNo evidence of external service failure during the Make step window.\n---\n7. Probable Root Cause\nPRIMARY ROOT CAUSE: Compile Failure in the Make Step\n\nThe build framework's buildex.py script invoked the UEFI firmware compilation for AthertonPkg (variants LAA/LAB) on agent san-w175-ha1-4-07. The Make step failed after ~2 min 31 sec of execution. The BuildInfoJson property was explicitly set to failedReason: Compile by the build framework, indicating the failure was detected within the compilation phase \u2014 not in packaging, artifact storage, or infrastructure.\n\nThe agent host had no resource constraints (CPU, memory, disk all healthy). The Commander nodes were healthy. External services were reachable (Setup succeeded). The failure is therefore attributable to a source code or build script error within the BOOT.XF.4.3 branch at revision 00263, spin 70.\n\nSupporting Evidence:\n\nBuildInfoJson: \"failedReason\":\"Compile\", \"status\":\"Failed\"\nCloudBees errorMessage: \"step 'Make' failed and its error handling aborted the job\"\nMake step duration: ~2m31s (partial compile, not a timeout \u2014 timeout was set to 5 hours)\nSetup step: exitCode 0 \u2014 environment was valid\nAgent host: No CPU/memory/disk exhaustion\nNo SCOM alerts on agent or Commander nodes\n---\n8. Confidence Level\nMEDIUM\u2013HIGH\nReason: The CloudBees job metadata and BuildInfoJson explicitly classify the failure as Compile. Infrastructure telemetry confirms no resource exhaustion on the agent. However, the specific compiler error lines (GCC/LLVM output) from the Make step log file (Make.<stepId>.log) were not directly accessible via Splunk, preventing identification of the exact failing source file, function, or error code. Confidence would be HIGH with direct Make step log access.\n\n---\n9. Infrastructure vs. Code Assessment\nInfrastructure Issue\tNO\nCode / Compile Issue\tYES\nMixed Issue\tNO\nReason: Agent host resources (CPU, memory, disk) were all within healthy ranges. No SCOM alerts. Commander nodes were healthy. The failure is explicitly classified as Compile by the build framework. The Make step ran for ~2.5 minutes before failing \u2014 consistent with a source code compilation error encountered mid-build, not an infrastructure timeout or resource exhaustion event.\n\n---\n10. Recommended Remediation\nExamine the Make step log directly: Retrieve Make.f179e25d-*.log from the CloudBees job workspace on san-w175-ha1-4-07 or from the build artifact location at /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds677/PROD/CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70. Look for GCC/LLVM/Python error lines.\nIdentify the failing source file: Search the Make log for patterns like error:, fatal error:, undefined reference, No such file or directory, or Python tracebacks from buildex.py.\nCheck recent code changes at revision 00263: Review commits to the BOOT.XF.4.3 branch at or near revision 00263 that affect AthertonPkg (LAA/LAB variants). Identify any changes to header files, build scripts, or toolchain configurations.\nVerify toolchain availability: Confirm Python 3.8.2 (/pkg/qct/software/ubuntu/python/3.8.2/bin) and all required build tools are present and functional on san-w175-ha1-4-07.\nRe-run the build after identifying and fixing the compile error. If the error is in a dependency (QcomToolsPkg, QcomTestPkg), fix the dependency first.\nMonitor /usr/vice/cache on san-w175-ha1-4-07 (currently at 72%) \u2014 clean up if approaching capacity.\n---\n11. Preventive Actions\nImplement pre-commit compile checks or incremental build validation for BOOT.XF.4.3 branch changes targeting AthertonPkg.\nEnable Splunk ingestion of CloudBees step-level logs (Make.*.log) to allow direct log-based RCA without requiring manual file retrieval.\nAdd a compile error pattern alert in Splunk/Datadog triggered when BuildInfoJson contains failedReason: Compile for CI builds.\nSet up disk usage monitoring alerts for /usr/vice/cache on build agents when utilization exceeds 80%.\nConsider build artifact retention policies to prevent workspace accumulation on /local/mnt.\n---\n12. Sources Used\nSource Type\tQuery Window\tEvidence Found\tRelevance\nSplunk \u2014 ecommander index\t-7d to now\tJob metadata, step sequence, BuildInfoJson, error messages, Commander node activity\tPRIMARY \u2014 direct CloudBees job evidence\nSplunk \u2014 os index (san-w175-ha1-4-07)\t-7d to now\tCPU utilization (very low), vmstat (load avg, page-out), disk usage (/local/mnt 3%, /usr/vice/cache 72%)\tAgent host health during build window\nSplunk \u2014 os index (las-colo12-j13-09)\t-7d to now\tMemory 18.2% used, disk healthy, load avg 1\u20137 (normal)\tCommander node health\nSCOM \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tActive alerts\tNo active alerts\tAgent host monitoring \u2014 confirmed healthy\nSCOM \u2014 las-colo12-j13-09/10/11\tActive alerts\tNo active alerts\tCommander node monitoring \u2014 confirmed healthy\n---",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_rca_f179e25d\",\"name\":\"RCA_f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010.txt\",\"description\":\"RCA log for CloudBees CI build/job f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010 / CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70, completed with error and abort status on 2026-07-07.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees procedure for job CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70_20260707_020049_020056 in project CRMBuilds.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_setup\",\"name\":\"Setup\",\"description\":\"Setup step ran on san-w175-ha1-4-07 from 2026-07-07 09:00:57Z to 09:01:19Z and completed successfully with exitCode 0.\"},{\"id\":\"step_make\",\"name\":\"Make\",\"description\":\"Primary failed step. Submitted on san-w175-ha1-4-07 at 2026-07-07 09:02:58Z and failed at 09:05:29Z after approximately 2 minutes 31 seconds, triggering abortJob.\"},{\"id\":\"step_savebuild\",\"name\":\"SaveBuild\",\"description\":\"Cascading failed step. Submitted at 2026-07-07 09:05:30Z and failed at 09:06:13Z after the Make failure.\"},{\"id\":\"step_downstream_packaging_postprocessing\",\"name\":\"Downstream packaging and post-processing steps\",\"description\":\"PreSave, PostSave, ConcurrentCopyPack, PackIt, NonParallelPack, HybridPackIt, HoldLinuxResource, NonParallelPackMake, ConcurrentCopyPackMake, PackMake, and CheckAbortCondition were canceled after the Make and SaveBuild failures.\"},{\"id\":\"step_posttimingstosplunk\",\"name\":\"PostTimingsToSplunk\",\"description\":\"alwaysRun step started at 2026-07-07 09:08:30Z and completed successfully at 2026-07-07 09:08:46Z.\"},{\"id\":\"step_buildinfojson_written\",\"name\":\"BuildInfoJson written\",\"description\":\"BuildInfoJson was written at 2026-07-07 09:08:39Z with status=Failed and failedReason=Compile.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_setup\",\"name\":\"Setup step\",\"description\":\"Environment setup and dependency reachability validation phase.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_compile_make\",\"name\":\"Compile / Make step\",\"description\":\"Compilation phase driven by boot_images/QcomPkg/buildex.py using Python 3.8.2 for UEFI firmware build targets including AthertonPkg.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_savebuild\",\"name\":\"SaveBuild step\",\"description\":\"Build artifact saving phase that depends on successful generation of valid build artifacts.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_packaging_postprocessing\",\"name\":\"Packaging and post-processing steps\",\"description\":\"Downstream packaging and post-processing phases canceled after upstream failure.\"}],\"log_symptoms\":[{\"id\":\"symptom_job_completed_error_abort\",\"name\":\"Job completed_error with ABORT status\",\"description\":\"CloudBees job outcome was error, combinedStatus was completed_error, and abortStatus was ABORT.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_make_failed_abortjob\",\"name\":\"Make step failed and triggered abortJob\",\"description\":\"CloudBees errorMessage recorded: \\\"step 'Make' failed and its error handling aborted the job\\\".\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_failedreason_compile\",\"name\":\"BuildInfoJson failedReason Compile\",\"description\":\"BuildInfoJson recorded status \\\"Failed\\\" and failedReason \\\"Compile\\\" for the CI build.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_savebuild_failed_cascade\",\"name\":\"SaveBuild failed after Make failure\",\"description\":\"CloudBees errorMessage recorded: \\\"step 'SaveBuild' failed and its error handling aborted the job\\\"; RCA states SaveBuild could not succeed without valid build artifacts.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_downstream_steps_canceled\",\"name\":\"Downstream steps canceled\",\"description\":\"All listed downstream packaging and post-processing steps were canceled rather than failed after the Make/SaveBuild failures.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_make_partial_compile_duration\",\"name\":\"Make ran for approximately 2m31s before failure\",\"description\":\"Make step duration was approximately 2 minutes 31 seconds, described as consistent with a partial compile and not a timeout; timeout was set to 5 hours.\"}],\"system_statuses\":[{\"id\":\"status_agent_resources_healthy\",\"name\":\"Agent host resources healthy\",\"description\":\"san-w175-ha1-4-07 showed no CPU, memory, swap, or /local/mnt disk exhaustion during the build window: CPU mostly idle, memory about 1.3\u20131.7% used, swap negligible, /local/mnt 3% used.\"},{\"id\":\"status_usr_vice_cache_elevated\",\"name\":\"/usr/vice/cache elevated but not full\",\"description\":\"On san-w175-ha1-4-07, /usr/vice/cache was 72% used (1.1G/1.5G), noted for monitoring but not full.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_scom_alerts_agent\",\"name\":\"No active SCOM alerts on agent\",\"description\":\"No active SCOM alerts were found on san-w175-ha1-4-07.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_concurrent_agent_jobs\",\"name\":\"No concurrent jobs found on agent\",\"description\":\"Available telemetry found no concurrent jobs on san-w175-ha1-4-07 during the build window.\"},{\"id\":\"status_commander_nodes_healthy\",\"name\":\"Commander infrastructure healthy\",\"description\":\"Commander nodes las-colo12-j13-09, las-colo12-j13-10, and las-colo12-j13-11 participated in orchestration; post-run steps completed successfully and no SCOM alerts were reported.\"},{\"id\":\"status_setup_external_services_reachable\",\"name\":\"External services reachable during Setup\",\"description\":\"Setup succeeded, confirming reachability at job start for oil.qualcomm.com, pcm.qualcomm.com, csds.qualcomm.com, verifysrc.qualcomm.com, apigw-op.qualcomm.com, and license-pdlm-1-encnaa.qualcomm.com.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_os_level_errors\",\"name\":\"No OS-level resource failure evidence\",\"description\":\"Splunk os/osetx telemetry found no OS-level errors, OOM events, or disk-full conditions during the build window.\"}],\"root_causes\":[{\"id\":\"root_cause_compile_failure_make\",\"name\":\"Compile failure in Make step\",\"description\":\"The primary root cause identified in the RCA is a source code or build script compile error within the buildex.py-driven UEFI firmware build for the AthertonPkg target, variants LAA/LAB, on BOOT.XF.4.3 branch revision 00263 spin 70. The failure is attributed to code/build script compilation because BuildInfoJson explicitly recorded failedReason=Compile and infrastructure telemetry was healthy.\"}],\"data_gaps\":[{\"id\":\"gap_make_step_log_unavailable\",\"name\":\"Make step log not directly accessible via Splunk\",\"description\":\"Specific compiler error messages, such as GCC/LLVM error lines, were stated to be in Make.<stepId>.log on the agent, but they were not directly accessible via Splunk telemetry.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_exact_failing_source_unknown\",\"name\":\"Exact failing source file/function/error code unknown\",\"description\":\"Because direct Make step log access was unavailable, the RCA could not identify the exact failing source file, function, compiler error, or error code.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_datadog_not_queried\",\"name\":\"No Datadog evidence collected\",\"description\":\"No Datadog queries were executed because no direct evidence linked Datadog alerts to this job ID, the agent host, or the Commander hosts.\"}],\"preventive_actions\":[{\"id\":\"preventive_precommit_compile_checks\",\"name\":\"Implement pre-commit compile checks\",\"description\":\"Implement pre-commit compile checks or incremental build validation for BOOT.XF.4.3 branch changes targeting AthertonPkg.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_ingest_step_logs\",\"name\":\"Enable Splunk ingestion of CloudBees step logs\",\"description\":\"Enable ingestion of CloudBees step-level logs such as Make.*.log into Splunk to support direct log-based RCA.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_compile_error_alert\",\"name\":\"Add compile error pattern alert\",\"description\":\"Add a Splunk/Datadog alert triggered when BuildInfoJson contains failedReason: Compile for CI builds.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_usr_vice_cache_alert\",\"name\":\"Monitor /usr/vice/cache above 80%\",\"description\":\"Set disk usage monitoring alerts for /usr/vice/cache on build agents when utilization exceeds 80%.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_artifact_retention_policy\",\"name\":\"Review build artifact retention policies\",\"description\":\"Consider build artifact retention policies to prevent workspace accumulation on /local/mnt.\"}],\"remediations\":[{\"id\":\"remediation_retrieve_make_log\",\"name\":\"Retrieve and examine Make step log\",\"description\":\"Retrieve Make.f179e25d-*.log from the CloudBees job workspace on san-w175-ha1-4-07 or from /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds677/PROD/CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70, then look for GCC/LLVM/Python error lines.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_identify_failing_source\",\"name\":\"Identify failing source file\",\"description\":\"Search the Make log for patterns including error:, fatal error:, undefined reference, No such file or directory, or Python tracebacks from buildex.py.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_review_revision_00263_changes\",\"name\":\"Review recent BOOT.XF.4.3 revision 00263 changes\",\"description\":\"Review commits at or near branch revision 00263 affecting AthertonPkg LAA/LAB variants, including header files, build scripts, or toolchain configuration changes.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_verify_toolchain\",\"name\":\"Verify toolchain availability\",\"description\":\"Confirm Python 3.8.2 at /pkg/qct/software/ubuntu/python/3.8.2/bin and all required build tools are present and functional on san-w175-ha1-4-07.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_rerun_after_fix\",\"name\":\"Re-run build after fixing compile error\",\"description\":\"Re-run the build after identifying and fixing the compile error; if the error is in a dependency such as QcomToolsPkg or QcomTestPkg, fix the dependency first.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_monitor_usr_vice_cache\",\"name\":\"Monitor and clean /usr/vice/cache if needed\",\"description\":\"Monitor /usr/vice/cache on san-w175-ha1-4-07, which was at 72%, and clean up if it approaches capacity.\"}],\"annotations\":[{\"id\":\"annotation_job_context\",\"name\":\"Job context\",\"description\":\"Job ID f179e25d-aec2-f1d3-9657-4efb9ff91010; job name CI_BOOT.XF.4.3-00263.1-ATHERTONLAZ-70_20260707_020049_020056; project CRMBuilds; outcome error; requester pawkuma; launched by tiberiumUserEC10_11.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_build_context\",\"name\":\"Build context\",\"description\":\"Software image BOOT.XF.4.3, branch revision 00263, spin 70, target AthertonPkg variants LAA and LAB on Ubuntu 16.04.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_execution_context\",\"name\":\"Execution context\",\"description\":\"Agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07, resource pool CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu16-04, workspace crm_ws_sd, build server drive G:, build location \\\\\\\\snowcone\\\\builds677\\\\PROD.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_build_script_targets\",\"name\":\"Build script and targets\",\"description\":\"Build script boot_images/QcomPkg/buildex.py using Python 3.8.2; build targets listed as AthertonPkg, QcomToolsPkg, QcomTestPkg, QcomSocPlatTestPkg, and QcomCatePkg.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_confidence\",\"name\":\"Confidence level MEDIUM-HIGH\",\"description\":\"RCA confidence was MEDIUM-HIGH because CloudBees metadata and BuildInfoJson classify the failure as Compile and infrastructure telemetry was healthy, but direct Make compiler error lines were unavailable.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_sources_used\",\"name\":\"Sources used\",\"description\":\"Sources cited include Splunk ecommander index, Splunk os index for san-w175-ha1-4-07 and las-colo12-j13-09, and SCOM active alert checks for agent and Commander nodes.\"}],\"relationships\":[{\"id\":\"rel_procedure_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Procedure extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179e25d\"},{\"id\":\"rel_setup_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Setup step extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_setup\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179e25d\"},{\"id\":\"re