    "file_name": "RCA_f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010.txt",
    "log_text": "Build ID: f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010\n---\n1. \ud83d\udccb Summary\nThe CloudBees build Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 failed due to a Compile Error in the Make step. The BuildMongr -makebuild command exited with exit code 4 after only 48 seconds, indicating a hard compile failure. The errorHandling=abortJob policy triggered an immediate job abort, cascading failures to the downstream VerifySrc (forcibly aborted) and SaveBuild (never executed) steps. No infrastructure-level issues were detected on the agent host crm-ubuntu345 or the CloudBees Commander. The root cause is a code/compile-level failure within the build invocation.\n\n---\n2. \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Job Context\nJob ID: f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010\nJob Name: Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2_20260707_002207_002213\nProject: CRMBuilds\nProcedure: Build.Rel.602829\nWorkflow Type: LEGACY\nOutcome: error\nAbort Status: ABORT\nFailed Reason: Compile\nLaunched By: tiberiumUserEC10_11\nBuilt By: gopu\nAgent Host: crm-ubuntu345 (Ubuntu 24.04, SanDiego)\nSoftware Image: Aurora.LA.3.1\nClient: STD.PROD\nEngineering Label: GLUE.AURORA_LA.3.0-00040-NOOP_TEST_AURORA-1\nBranch Point Revision: 00151\nSpin: 2\nBuild Delete Date: 2026-07-10\n---\n3. \ud83d\udd50 Build Timeline\nTime (UTC)\tStep\tStatus\tDuration\tExit Code\tHost\n07:22:13Z\tJob Start\t\u2705 Running\t\u2014\t\u2014\tcrm-ubuntu345\n07:22:13Z \u2013 07:22:28Z\tSetup\t\u2705 Success\t15s\t0\tcrm-ubuntu345\n07:23:57Z \u2013 07:24:45Z\tMake (stepIndex 10)\t\u274c FAILED\t48s\t4\tcrm-ubuntu345\n07:24:45Z\tVerifySrc\t\u26a0\ufe0f ABORTED (cascade)\t\u2014\tABORTED\tcrm-ubuntu345\n07:24:45Z\tSaveBuild\t\u26d4 NEVER RAN\t\u2014\t\u2014\t\u2014\n07:26:xx \u2013 07:28:27Z\tCleanup/Finalization Steps (GenerateProvenance, Finalize, AddManifest, CleanUp, Record_All_Times, Calculate Metrics, etc.)\t\u2705 Success (alwaysRun/ignore)\t~2 min\t0\tcrm-ubuntu345 / crm-ubuntu327 / crm-ubuntu332 / crm-ubuntu309\n07:28:27Z\tJob End\tcompleted_error\t374s total\t\u2014\t\u2014\n---\n4. \ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f Execution Path Inventory\nFailed Step: Make (stepId: f179d493-2a0c-f119-a58d-2686f9881e6f) \u2014 BuildMongr -makebuild Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2\nAgent Host: crm-ubuntu345 (Ubuntu 24.04, SanDiego, CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu24-04 pool, PROXY zone)\nCommander Host: No direct evidence of Commander contribution to failure\nInvoked Build Tool: BuildMongr (internal build orchestration tool)\nBuild Artifact Location: /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds907/PROD/Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 / \\\\snowcone\\builds907\\PROD\nImage Components (SanDiego): CPUCP, AOP, BTFW, WLAN, TZ, DSP, BOOT, QSSI, GLUE\nImage Components (LasVegas): DISPLAY, GRAPHICS, KERNEL, VIDEO, CAMERA, LA.VENDOR\n---\n5. \ud83d\udea8 Detected Error Codes\nStep\tExit Code\tMeaning\tEvidence\nMake\t4\tCompile failure (non-zero exit from BuildMongr indicating build/make error)\tSplunk ecommander index \u2014 stepId f179d493-2a0c-f119-a58d-2686f9881e6f\nVerifySrc\tABORTED\tCascaded abort triggered by Make step's errorHandling=abortJob\tSplunk ecommander index \u2014 stepId f179d493-29e5-f107-a58d-2686f9881e6f\nSaveBuild\t\u2014\tNever executed \u2014 job aborted before this step could run\tSplunk ecommander index \u2014 stepId f179d493-2a33-f12d-a58d-2686f9881e6f\n---\n6. \ud83d\udd17 Correlated Observations\n\u2601\ufe0f CloudBees\nJob f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010 confirmed failed with outcome=error, abortStatus=ABORT, failedReason=Compile.\nThe Make step (stepIndex 10) ran for only 48 seconds before exiting with code 4 \u2014 a very short duration for a full build, strongly indicating an early compile-time failure.\nerrorHandling=abortJob was set on the Make step, which is the direct trigger for the job abort cascade.\nThe Setup step completed successfully (exit code 0, 15s), confirming the environment was initialized correctly.\nAll post-failure cleanup steps (GenerateProvenance, Finalize, AddManifest, CleanUp, Record_All_Times, Calculate Metrics) completed successfully with errorHandling=ignore and alwaysRun=true.\n\ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Agent Host: crm-ubuntu345\nAgent is part of the CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu24-04 resource pool, PROXY zone, SanDiego site.\nAgent version: 2024.12.0.177508 \u2014 current and healthy.\nPool activity logs show crm-ubuntu344 had stepCount=2 with stepLimit=9 \u2014 pool was not saturated.\nA concurrent job (Snapdragon_Auto.HGY.4.1.8.0.r1-00018.02-STD.INT-1) was later observed running successfully on crm-ubuntu345, confirming the agent itself was functional.\nNo SCOM alerts were found for crm-ubuntu345.\nNo Datadog logs were found for crm-ubuntu345 during the failure window (no telemetry coverage in Datadog for this host).\nNo OS-level (Splunk os/osetx index) logs were available for this host during the failure window.\n\ud83c\udfdb\ufe0f Commander Host\nNo evidence of Commander-side failures contributing to the job failure.\nJob scheduling, resource assignment, and step dispatch all functioned normally (Setup step succeeded).\n\ud83d\udcca Datadog\nNo Datadog logs found for host crm-ubuntu345 during the failure window (07:20Z\u201307:30Z).\nNo telemetry coverage available in Datadog for this agent host.\n\ud83d\udcc1 Splunk\nSplunk ecommander index provided full job metadata, step details, exit codes, and timing \u2014 primary evidence source.\nNo OS/system-level logs (os/osetx indexes) available for crm-ubuntu345 during the failure window.\nNo BuildMongr-specific error log entries were found beyond the exit code 4 recorded in the CloudBees step metadata.\n\ud83d\udd0c External Dependencies\nBuildMongr: The build orchestration tool invoked by the Make step. Exit code 4 is the direct failure signal. No external service connectivity issues were detected.\nsnowcone (build artifact storage): No evidence of storage failures. Artifact path was pre-configured and cleanup steps ran successfully.\nLasVegas components: DISPLAY, GRAPHICS, KERNEL, VIDEO, CAMERA, LA.VENDOR were part of the build. No evidence of remote component fetch failures.\n---\n7. \ud83c\udfaf Probable Root Cause\nThe Make step invoked BuildMongr -makebuild Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 and exited with exit code 4 after only 48 seconds. The CloudBees job metadata explicitly records failedReason=Compile, confirming this is a compile-time failure within the build process.\n\nThe most probable root cause is a compilation error in one or more source components of the Aurora.LA.3.1 image (spanning SanDiego and LasVegas components). The short 48-second runtime before failure suggests the error occurred early in the compilation phase \u2014 possibly a missing symbol, syntax error, incompatible header, or dependency resolution failure within the source tree associated with engineering label GLUE.AURORA_LA.3.0-00040-NOOP_TEST_AURORA-1 at branch point revision 00151.\n\nSupporting Evidence:\n\nExit code 4 from BuildMongr (non-zero, indicating build failure)\nCloudBees metadata: failedReason=Compile\nStep duration: only 48 seconds (abnormally short for a full build)\nAgent and infrastructure were healthy (Setup succeeded, no SCOM alerts, agent ran other jobs successfully)\nCascade abort of VerifySrc and SaveBuild confirms no further build artifacts were produced\n---\n8. \ud83d\udcc8 Confidence Level\nMEDIUM\n\nReason: The CloudBees metadata explicitly states failedReason=Compile and exit code 4 from BuildMongr, providing strong direct evidence of a compile failure. However, the specific compile error message (e.g., which file, which component, which error) is not available in Splunk or Datadog \u2014 the detailed BuildMongr log output would need to be examined directly from the build workspace at /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds907/PROD/Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 to achieve HIGH confidence.\n\n---\n9. \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\nInfrastructure Issue\tNO\nCode Issue\tYES\nMixed\tNO\nReason: The agent host crm-ubuntu345 was healthy (no SCOM alerts, agent ran other jobs successfully, Setup step passed). The failure is explicitly classified as Compile by CloudBees, and exit code 4 from BuildMongr is a build-tool-level failure, not an infrastructure-level signal. No storage, network, DNS, or resource exhaustion indicators were found.\n\n---\n10. \ud83d\udd27 Recommended Remediation\nExamine BuildMongr logs directly at the build workspace:\n/prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds907/PROD/Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2\nLook for the specific compile error (file, line, error message) before the build delete date of 2026-07-10.\nReview recent changes to engineering label GLUE.AURORA_LA.3.0-00040-NOOP_TEST_AURORA-1 at branch point revision 00151 \u2014 identify any recent commits that may have introduced a compile-breaking change.\nCheck component compatibility between SanDiego components (CPUCP, AOP, BTFW, WLAN, TZ, DSP, BOOT, QSSI, GLUE) and LasVegas components (DISPLAY, GRAPHICS, KERNEL, VIDEO, CAMERA, LA.VENDOR) for API/header mismatches.\nRe-run the build after identifying and fixing the compile error, or roll back the offending commit.\nContact the build owner (gopu) with the specific error details for code-level remediation.\n---\n11. \ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Preventive Actions\nPre-submit compile checks: Enforce pre-submit build validation on the GLUE/Aurora component tree to catch compile errors before they reach the full integration build.\nBuildMongr log forwarding: Configure BuildMongr to forward detailed compile error logs to Splunk or Datadog for faster RCA without needing direct filesystem access.\nExit code documentation: Document BuildMongr exit codes (especially code 4) in the team's runbook to accelerate triage.\nIncrease build delete retention: Consider extending the build delete date beyond 3 days for failed builds to allow more time for post-mortem log analysis.\nComponent integration testing: Add automated compatibility checks between SanDiego and LasVegas component sets before triggering full image builds.\n---\n12. \ud83d\udcda Sources Used\nSource Type\tQuery Window\tEvidence\tRelevance\nSplunk (ecommander index)\t2026-07-07T07:20Z \u2013 07:30Z\tFull job metadata, step details, exit codes, timing, agent assignment, component list\tPRIMARY \u2014 direct CloudBees job execution data\nSplunk (ecommander index)\t-7d\tResource pool activity, concurrent jobs on crm-ubuntu345, agent version\tAgent health and concurrency context\nSplunk (os/osetx indexes)\t2026-07-07T07:20Z \u2013 07:30Z\tNo results \u2014 no OS-level logs available for crm-ubuntu345\tAttempted agent host system-level telemetry\nDatadog Logs\t2026-07-07T07:20Z \u2013 07:30Z\tNo results \u2014 no Datadog coverage for crm-ubuntu345\tAttempted agent host application-level telemetry\nSCOM\tCurrent\tNo active alerts for crm-ubuntu345\tAgent host infrastructure health check\n---",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_rca_f179d493\",\"name\":\"RCA_f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010.txt\",\"description\":\"Source RCA log for CloudBees build/job f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010, build Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"proc_build_rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees procedure for job Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2_20260707_002207_002213 in project CRMBuilds. Workflow type LEGACY; outcome=error; abortStatus=ABORT; failedReason=Compile.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_setup\",\"name\":\"Setup\",\"description\":\"Setup step on crm-ubuntu345 from 07:22:13Z to 07:22:28Z. Completed successfully in 15 seconds with exit code 0.\"},{\"id\":\"step_make\",\"name\":\"Make\",\"description\":\"Failed step with stepId f179d493-2a0c-f119-a58d-2686f9881e6f and stepIndex 10. Ran BuildMongr -makebuild Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 on crm-ubuntu345 from 07:23:57Z to 07:24:45Z. Failed after 48 seconds with exit code 4. errorHandling=abortJob triggered job abort cascade.\"},{\"id\":\"step_verifysrc\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Step with stepId f179d493-29e5-f107-a58d-2686f9881e6f. Forcibly aborted at 07:24:45Z due to cascade from Make step failure.\"},{\"id\":\"step_savebuild\",\"name\":\"SaveBuild\",\"description\":\"Step with stepId f179d493-2a33-f12d-a58d-2686f9881e6f. Never executed because the job was aborted before this step could run.\"},{\"id\":\"step_cleanup_finalization\",\"name\":\"Cleanup/Finalization Steps\",\"description\":\"Post-failure steps including GenerateProvenance, Finalize, AddManifest, CleanUp, Record_All_Times, Calculate Metrics, and related steps. Ran approximately 07:26xxZ to 07:28:27Z and succeeded with alwaysRun/errorHandling=ignore behavior on crm-ubuntu345, crm-ubuntu327, crm-ubuntu332, and crm-ubuntu309.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_setup\",\"name\":\"Setup\",\"description\":\"Environment initialization step class.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_makebuild\",\"name\":\"Make Build\",\"description\":\"Build invocation step class using BuildMongr internal build orchestration.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_verification\",\"name\":\"Source Verification\",\"description\":\"Source verification step class.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_savebuild\",\"name\":\"Save Build Artifact\",\"description\":\"Build artifact saving/publishing step class.\"},{\"id\":\"step_class_cleanup_finalization\",\"name\":\"Cleanup and Finalization\",\"description\":\"Post-failure cleanup, metrics, manifest, provenance, and finalization step class.\"}],\"log_symptoms\":[{\"id\":\"symptom_job_failed_compile\",\"name\":\"Job failed with Compile reason\",\"description\":\"CloudBees job f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010 had outcome=error, abortStatus=ABORT, and failedReason=Compile.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_make_exit_code_4\",\"name\":\"Make step exited with code 4\",\"description\":\"Make step exited after 48 seconds with exit code 4 from BuildMongr, recorded in Splunk ecommander metadata.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_short_make_duration\",\"name\":\"Make step failed after 48 seconds\",\"description\":\"Make step duration was only 48 seconds, described in the RCA as abnormally short for a full build and consistent with an early compile-time failure.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_abort_cascade\",\"name\":\"Abort cascade after Make failure\",\"description\":\"Make step errorHandling=abortJob caused downstream VerifySrc to be aborted and SaveBuild to never run.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_no_buildmongr_error_details\",\"name\":\"No detailed BuildMongr error entries found\",\"description\":\"Splunk and Datadog did not contain BuildMongr-specific error log entries beyond the exit code 4 recorded in CloudBees step metadata.\"}],\"system_statuses\":[{\"id\":\"status_agent_setup_success\",\"name\":\"Agent environment initialized successfully\",\"description\":\"Setup step completed successfully with exit code 0 in 15 seconds on crm-ubuntu345.\"},{\"id\":\"status_agent_healthy\",\"name\":\"Agent host crm-ubuntu345 healthy\",\"description\":\"crm-ubuntu345 was in CRMBuildsLinux-Ubuntu24-04 pool, PROXY zone, SanDiego site. RCA states agent version 2024.12.0.177508 was current and healthy, no SCOM alerts were found, and another job later ran successfully on the same host.\"},{\"id\":\"status_pool_not_saturated\",\"name\":\"Resource pool not saturated\",\"description\":\"Pool activity logs showed crm-ubuntu344 had stepCount=2 with stepLimit=9; RCA states pool was not saturated.\"},{\"id\":\"status_commander_no_failure_evidence\",\"name\":\"No Commander-side failure evidence\",\"description\":\"RCA states no evidence of Commander-side failures contributed to the job failure; scheduling, resource assignment, and step dispatch functioned normally.\"},{\"id\":\"status_storage_no_failure_evidence\",\"name\":\"No storage failure evidence\",\"description\":\"RCA states there was no evidence of snowcone build artifact storage failures and cleanup steps ran successfully.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_external_connectivity_issue_detected\",\"name\":\"No external service c␀nnectivity issue detected\",\"description\":\"RCA states no external service connectivity issues were detected for BuildMongr or related dependencies.\"}],\"root_causes\":[{\"id\":\"root_cause_compile_failure\",\"name\":\"Code/compile-level failure in BuildMongr Make invocation\",\"description\":\"Most probable root cause: compilation error in one or more source components of the Aurora.LA.3.1 image during BuildMongr -makebuild Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2. Evidence includes CloudBees failedReason=Compile, BuildMongr exit code 4, 48-second Make duration, healthy infrastructure indicators, and downstream abort cascade. Specific file/component/error is not available in the provided evidence.\"}],\"data_gaps\":[{\"id\":\"gap_specific_compile_error\",\"name\":\"Specific compile error unavailable\",\"description\":\"The RCA does not include the exact compiler error message, file, line, component, missing symbol, syntax error, header mismatch, or dependency error.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_buildmongr_detailed_logs\",\"name\":\"Detailed BuildMongr logs not captured in telemetry\",\"description\":\"No BuildMongr-specific error log entries were found in Splunk or Datadog beyond CloudBees metadata exit code 4. The RCA says detailed BuildMongr output must be examined directly from the build workspace.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_datadog_coverage\",\"name\":\"No Datadog coverage for crm-ubuntu345 during failure window\",\"description\":\"Datadog Logs returned no results for crm-ubuntu345 during 2026-07-07T07:20Z\u201307:30Z; RCA states no telemetry coverage was available for this agent host.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_os_logs\",\"name\":\"No OS-level logs for crm-ubuntu345 during failure window\",\"description\":\"Splunk os/osetx indexes had no OS/system-level logs for crm-ubuntu345 during 2026-07-07T07:20Z\u201307:30Z.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_exact_commander_host_evidence\",\"name\":\"No direct Commander contribution evidence\",\"description\":\"RCA states there was no direct evidence of Commander contribution to the failure; only normal scheduling/resource assignment/step dispatch behavior is reported.\"}],\"preventive_actions\":[{\"id\":\"pa_presubmit_compile_checks\",\"name\":\"Enforce pre-submit compile checks\",\"description\":\"Enforce pre-submit build validation on the GLUE/Aurora component tree to catch compile errors before full integration builds.\"},{\"id\":\"pa_buildmongr_log_forwarding\",\"name\":\"Forward detailed BuildMongr logs\",\"description\":\"Configure BuildMongr to forward detailed compile error logs to Splunk or Datadog for faster RCA without direct filesystem access.\"},{\"id\":\"pa_exit_code_documentation\",\"name\":\"Document BuildMongr exit codes\",\"description\":\"Document BuildMongr exit codes, especially code 4, in the team runbook to accelerate triage.\"},{\"id\":\"pa_extend_retention\",\"name\":\"Increase failed-build retention\",\"description\":\"Consider extending build delete retention beyond 3 days for failed builds to allow more time for post-mortem log analysis.\"},{\"id\":\"pa_component_integration_testing\",\"name\":\"Add component compatibility checks\",\"description\":\"Add automated compatibility checks between SanDiego and LasVegas component sets before full image builds.\"}],\"remediations\":[{\"id\":\"rem_examine_buildmongr_logs\",\"name\":\"Examine BuildMongr workspace logs\",\"description\":\"Inspect detailed BuildMongr logs directly at /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds907/PROD/Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 before build delete date 2026-07-10 to find the specific compile error.\"},{\"id\":\"rem_review_recent_changes\",\"name\":\"Review recent source changes\",\"description\":\"Review recent changes to engineering label GLUE.AURORA_LA.3.0-00040-NOOP_TEST_AURORA-1 at branch point revision 00151 to identify compile-breaking commits.\"},{\"id\":\"rem_check_component_compatibility\",\"name\":\"Check SanDiego and LasVegas component compatibility\",\"description\":\"Check compatibility between SanDiego components CPUCP, AOP, BTFW, WLAN, TZ, DSP, BOOT, QSSI, GLUE and LasVegas components DISPLAY, GRAPHICS, KERNEL, VIDEO, CAMERA, LA.VENDOR for API/header mismatches.\"},{\"id\":\"rem_rerun_or_rollback\",\"name\":\"Fix and rerun or roll back offending change\",\"description\":\"After identifying and fixing the compile error, rerun the build; alternatively roll back the offending commit.\"},{\"id\":\"rem_contact_build_owner\",\"name\":\"Contact build owner\",\"description\":\"Contact build owner gopu with the specific error details for code-level remediation.\"}],\"annotations\":[{\"id\":\"ann_confidence_medium\",\"name\":\"Confidence Level: MEDIUM\",\"description\":\"The RCA confidence is MEDIUM because CloudBees metadata and BuildMongr exit code strongly indicate compile failure, but the specific compile error details are unavailable.\"},{\"id\":\"ann_infrastructure_vs_code\",\"name\":\"Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\",\"description\":\"Infrastructure Issue=NO; Code Issue=YES; Mixed=NO. Reason: agent host was healthy, Setup passed, no SCOM alerts, another job ran successfully, and CloudBees classified failure as Compile.\"},{\"id\":\"ann_build_context\",\"name\":\"Build context\",\"description\":\"Build ID f179d493-1daf-f1fc-91e4-4efb9ff91010; job name Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2_20260707_002207_002213; project CRMBuilds; launched by tiberiumUserEC10_11; built by gopu; agent host crm-ubuntu345; software image Aurora.LA.3.1; client STD.PROD; branch point revision 00151; spin 2.\"},{\"id\":\"ann_artifact_location\",\"name\":\"Build artifact location\",\"description\":\"Configured build artifact location: /prj/qct/asw/crmbuilds/snowcone/builds907/PROD/Aurora.LA.3.1-00151-STD.PROD-2 and \\\\\\\\snowcone\\\\builds907\\\\PROD.\"},{\"id\":\"ann_primary_source\",\"name\":\"Primary evidence source\",\"description\":\"Splunk ecommander index provided job metadata, step details, exit codes, timing, agent assignment, and component list for 2026-07-07T07:20Z\u201307:30Z.\"}],\"relationships\":[{\"id\":\"rel_proc_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Procedure extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"proc_build_rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179d493\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_setup_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Setup step extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_setup\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179d493\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_make_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Make step extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_make\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179d493\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_verifysrc_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc step extracted from source RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verifysrc\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179d493\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_savebuild_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"SaveBuild step extracted from source