    "file_name": "RCA_f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f.txt",
    "log_text": "Root Cause Analysis Report\nJob ID: f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f  |  Build: WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2  |  Outcome: ERROR / ABORTED\n\n---\n1. Executive Summary\nCloudBees job f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f failed during the \"VerifySrc\" step with exit code 2 on agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07. The CloudBees execution context classifies the failure reason as \"Aborted\" \u2014 the step was externally terminated before natural completion.\n\nThis job shares the same step name (VerifySrc), exit code (2), failure reason (Aborted), and procedure (Build.Rel.602829) as the previous job on san-w175-ja4-6-06, but the infrastructure signature is distinctly different:\n\nNo large inbound network burst \u2014 unlike the previous job's 257MB download, this host received only ~1.2\u20131.4MB/s during the step. The source fetch pattern is absent.\nMassive outbound network burst \u2014 55MB \u2192 40MB \u2192 54MB \u2192 107MB \u2192 98MB sent during the step window (~354MB total outbound in ~77 seconds). This is the dominant infrastructure signal.\nIO contention pre-step \u2014 IO await peaked at 15.97ms and IO util at 15.97% at ~06:19:23Z, 27 seconds before the step started. This indicates the storage subsystem was already under load from a prior or concurrent operation when VerifySrc began.\nRising system load \u2014 load average climbed steadily from 0.81 \u2192 1.97 throughout the window, indicating accumulating process pressure, consistent with concurrent workloads on the agent.\nCPU abrupt drop to 0.07% at the end of the step \u2014 consistent with process termination (abort signal).\nProbable Root Cause: The VerifySrc step was aborted due to a combination of pre-existing IO contention (storage subsystem already stressed before step start) and a large outbound data transfer (~354MB) that saturated the agent's upload bandwidth or triggered a network/transfer timeout. The step likely attempted to upload or push source verification artifacts/results to a remote endpoint. The transfer stalled or exceeded a timeout threshold, triggering an abort. Exit code 2 and \"Aborted\" classification confirm external termination.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f No application-level logs are forwarded from san-w175-ha1-4-07 to Datadog. The Datadog Agent is installed and reporting metrics, but no log pipeline is configured. Step-level stdout/stderr must be retrieved directly from CloudBees to confirm the exact abort trigger and the destination of the outbound transfer.\n\n---\n2. Job Context\nJob ID: f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f\nJob Name: WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2_20260706_231638_231652\nProject: CRMBuilds\nProcedure: Build.Rel.602829\nOutcome: completed_error / error\nFailed Step: VerifySrc (Step ID: f179cb72-2ade-f1e2-b856-2686f9881e6f)\nExit Code: 2 \u2014 script-level abort / explicit exit 2 on detected error condition\nAgent Host: san-w175-ha1-4-07 (GNU/Linux, Datadog Agent 7.64.1 \u2705)\nBuild Name: WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2\nDeclared Failure Reason: Aborted\nBuild Type: WLAN TFH 3.6.c2 (Thin Firmware Host, older branch) \u2014 QCATFSWPZ variant\nAgent Rack: san-w175-ha1 \u2014 20 hosts registered in Datadog, all Agent 7.64.1 GNU/Linux\n---\n3. Build Timeline\nTime (UTC)\tEvent\tDetail\n2026-07-07 06:16:52\tJob Started\tCRMBuilds / Build.Rel.602829 initiated on san-w175-ha1-4-07\n~2026-07-07 06:19:14\u201306:19:32\t\u26a1 Pre-Step IO Contention\tIO await peaks at 15.97ms, IO util at 15.97%, CPU iowait spikes to 0.129% \u2014 storage subsystem under load before VerifySrc starts. Concurrent workload suspected.\n~2026-07-07 06:19:11\tLarge Outbound Transfer Begins\tNetwork bytes_sent: 9.4MB \u2192 drops \u2192 then massive burst begins. System load starts rising from 0.81.\n2026-07-07 06:19:50\tVerifySrc Step Started\tStep begins \u2014 Correlation Window Opens. IO contention already present. Load at ~1.03.\n~2026-07-07 06:19:59\u201306:20:44\t\u26a1 Massive Outbound Burst During Step\tbytes_sent: 55MB \u2192 40MB \u2192 54MB \u2192 107MB \u2192 98MB in successive intervals. Total ~354MB outbound. System load rises to 1.97. CPU user peaks at 1.27%.\n~2026-07-07 06:20:53\u201306:21:07\tCPU Drops Abruptly\tCPU user falls from ~1.02% to 0.07% \u2014 process terminated. Load begins declining from 1.97 \u2192 1.55.\n2026-07-07 06:21:07\tVerifySrc Step ABORTED\tExit Code 2 \u2014 step terminated \u2014 Correlation Window Closes (duration: ~1m 17s)\n2026-07-07 06:25:54\tJob Ended\tJob terminates with outcome: error (4m 47s after step abort \u2014 cleanup/teardown phase)\n---\n4. Execution Path Inventory\nFailed Step: \"VerifySrc\" \u2014 source verification step; on this host, dominated by a large outbound transfer (~354MB sent), suggesting upload of source verification data or artifacts to a remote endpoint\nAgent Host: san-w175-ha1-4-07 (GNU/Linux, Datadog Agent 7.64.1 \u2014 metrics available, no log pipeline)\nCommander Host: Not identified \u2014 no evidence of Commander contribution to failure\nInvoked Services: Remote endpoint receiving the large outbound transfer (Artifactory, SCM, or build coordination server \u2014 specific endpoint not available from metadata); local storage subsystem on san-w175-ha1-4-07\nConcurrent Workloads: Rising system load (0.81 \u2192 1.97) and pre-step IO contention strongly suggest at least one other concurrent process running on this agent during the step\n---\n5. Detected Error Codes & Signals\nCode / Signal\tSource\tMeaning\tEvidence\nExit Code 2\tCloudBees Step Metadata\tScript-level abort \u2014 explicit exit 2 on detected error, or return code from a failed transfer utility (e.g., rsync protocol error, scp failure, curl partial transfer). Identical to previous job's exit code.\tfailedStep.exitCode = \"2\"\nAborted\tCloudBees executionContext\tStep terminated before natural completion \u2014 timeout, external signal, or explicit abort in script\texecutionContext.failedReason = \"Aborted\"\nIO Await 15.97ms (pre-step)\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tStorage device wait time peaked at 15.97ms at ~06:19:23Z \u2014 27 seconds before step start. Indicates a concurrent workload was already stressing the storage subsystem when VerifySrc began.\tsystem.io.await peak at point 3 (~06:19:23Z), 9s interval series\nIO Util 15.97% (pre-step)\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tStorage utilization at 15.97% before step start \u2014 elevated baseline entering the step\tsystem.io.util peak at point 3 (~06:19:23Z)\nOutbound Burst ~354MB\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\t55MB + 40MB + 54MB + 107MB + 98MB sent in successive ~9s intervals during the step. Total ~354MB outbound in ~45 seconds. Dominant infrastructure signal \u2014 no equivalent inbound burst.\tsystem.net.bytes_sent peaks during step window\nRising System Load 0.81\u21921.97\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tLoad average rose steadily throughout the window \u2014 consistent with accumulating concurrent processes, many in IO-wait or runnable state\tsystem.load.1 rising from 0.81 \u2192 1.97 across 24 data points\nCPU Abrupt Drop to 0.07%\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tCPU user dropped from ~1.02% to 0.07% at end of step \u2014 process terminated (abort signal or script exit)\tsystem.cpu.user sharp decline at final data points\nCPU Stolen = 0\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tNo hypervisor CPU theft \u2014 VM-level resource contention is NOT a contributing factor\tsystem.cpu.stolen = 0 throughout\n---\n6. Correlated Observations\nCloudBees\nStep \"VerifySrc\" failed with exit code 2 and failure reason \"Aborted\" \u2014 identical signature to the previous WLAN TFH job on san-w175-ja4-6-06\nStep duration: ~1m 17s \u2014 slightly longer than the previous job's ~1m 5s, consistent with a larger or slower transfer before abort\nJob total duration: ~9m 2s \u2014 significantly longer than the step duration, indicating substantial pre-step and post-step activity (setup, cleanup, teardown)\nBuild type WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2 \u2014 older WLAN TFH branch; QCATFSWPZ variant\nConfidence: HIGH \u2014 directly from job payload\nAgent Host (san-w175-ha1-4-07) \u2014 KEY FINDINGS\n\u2705 Datadog Agent 7.64.1 installed \u2014 full metric telemetry available\n\nIO Subsystem \u2014 Pre-Step Contention:\n\nIO await peaked at 15.97ms at ~06:19:23Z \u2014 27 seconds before VerifySrc started. This is a pre-existing IO load, not caused by the VerifySrc step itself.\nIO util peaked at 15.97% simultaneously \u2014 elevated but not fully saturated\nCPU iowait spiked to 0.129% at the same point \u2014 processes were blocked on IO before the step began\nIO metrics settled to 0.05\u20133.79% during the step itself \u2014 the pre-step IO burst subsided, but the storage device was already in a degraded state entering the step\nContrast with previous job (san-w175-ja4-6-06): That job had IO contention during the step (35.7ms peak) caused by a large inbound download. This job had IO contention before the step from a concurrent workload, with the step itself dominated by outbound traffic.\nNetwork \u2014 Dominant Outbound Transfer:\n\n~354MB sent during the step window in 5 successive bursts: 55MB \u2192 40MB \u2192 54MB \u2192 107MB \u2192 98MB\nOnly ~1.2\u20131.5MB received during the step \u2014 no large source download. This is the opposite pattern from the previous job.\nThe outbound burst pattern suggests the VerifySrc step was uploading source verification data, build artifacts, or a source tree to a remote endpoint (Artifactory, build server, or SCM)\nThe transfer was interrupted mid-stream (CPU drops abruptly while outbound traffic was still active) \u2014 consistent with a timeout or abort signal during upload\nSystem Load \u2014 Concurrent Workload Evidence:\n\nLoad average rose from 0.81 \u2192 1.97 across the entire window \u2014 a steady, sustained increase\nThis pattern is characteristic of multiple concurrent processes accumulating on the agent, not a single step's activity\nCPU user remained low (0.1\u20131.27%) while load was high \u2014 consistent with processes in IO-wait or runnable-but-blocked state\nMemory: 392\u2013393GB usable \u2014 no memory pressure whatsoever\nDisk: 42.1% used \u2014 healthy, no disk exhaustion\nCPU stolen: 0% \u2014 no hypervisor contention\nComparison with Previous Job (san-w175-ja4-6-06):\n\nSignal\tsan-w175-ja4-6-06 (prev job)\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07 (this job)\nIO await peak\t35.7ms (during step)\t15.97ms (pre-step)\nNetwork inbound\t257MB received (large download)\t~1.4MB (minimal)\nNetwork outbound\t144MB sent (post-step)\t~354MB sent (during step)\nSystem load peak\t2.04\t1.97\nPrimary failure mode\tIO contention during download write\tUpload timeout/abort during outbound transfer\nExit code\t2\t2\nFailure reason\tAborted\tAborted\nCommander Host\nNo Commander host identified in job metadata\nNo Commander-related errors found in logs during the correlation window\nOUT_OF_SCOPE\nDatadog \u2014 Logs\nZero log entries from san-w175-ha1-4-07 \u2014 Datadog Agent installed but no log pipeline configured\nZero Artifactory LDAP errors during this job's window \u2014 LDAP is NOT a contributing factor\nZero active incidents during the job execution window\nNo monitors configured for san-w175-ha1-4-07\nExternal Dependencies \u2014 SCOPE VALIDATION\nArtifactory LDAP failures \u2014 Zero occurrences during this job's window. OUT_OF_SCOPE\nRemote upload endpoint \u2014 The destination of the ~354MB outbound transfer is unknown from available metadata. This endpoint (Artifactory, SCM, or build server) is in the execution path but cannot be identified without step logs.\n---\n7. Probable Root Cause\nPrimary: Large Outbound Transfer Timeout/Abort During VerifySrc Upload Phase\n\nThe VerifySrc step initiated a large outbound transfer (~354MB) to a remote endpoint. The agent's storage subsystem was already under IO contention from a concurrent workload (IO await 15.97ms pre-step). The combination of pre-existing IO pressure and a sustained large upload (~354MB in ~45 seconds) caused the transfer to stall or exceed a timeout threshold. The VerifySrc script detected the failure condition and exited with code 2. CloudBees classified this as \"Aborted.\"\n\nCausal Chain:\n\nA concurrent workload on san-w175-ha1-4-07 creates IO contention (15.97ms await) before VerifySrc starts\nVerifySrc step starts at 06:19:50Z with the storage subsystem already stressed\nStep initiates a large outbound transfer (~354MB) \u2014 likely uploading source verification data or artifacts to a remote endpoint\nThe upload proceeds but encounters a stall \u2014 possibly due to network congestion, remote endpoint slowness, or local IO contention affecting read throughput for the upload\nTransfer exceeds a timeout threshold OR the remote endpoint rejects/drops the connection\nVerifySrc script detects failure \u2192 exits with code 2\nCloudBees marks step as failed with reason \"Aborted\"\nSupporting Evidence:\n\nIO await 15.97ms at ~06:19:23Z \u2014 pre-step IO contention from concurrent workload (Datadog system.io.await)\n~354MB outbound burst during step window (Datadog system.net.bytes_sent)\nOnly ~1.4MB inbound \u2014 no large download, upload is the dominant operation (Datadog system.net.bytes_rcvd)\nSystem load rising 0.81 \u2192 1.97 \u2014 concurrent process accumulation (Datadog system.load.1)\nCPU abrupt drop to 0.07% \u2014 process terminated (Datadog system.cpu.user)\nExit code 2 + failedReason \"Aborted\" \u2014 external termination confirmed (CloudBees metadata)\nCPU stolen = 0% \u2014 hypervisor contention excluded (Datadog system.cpu.stolen)\nMemory 392GB usable, disk 42.1% \u2014 resource exhaustion excluded\n---\n8. Confidence Level\n\u2705 MEDIUM\n\nHIGH confidence that the step was aborted \u2014 exit code 2 + \"Aborted\" + abrupt CPU drop are unambiguous\nHIGH confidence that a large outbound transfer (~354MB) occurred during the step \u2014 direct metric evidence\nHIGH confidence that pre-step IO contention existed from a concurrent workload\nMEDIUM confidence on the specific abort trigger \u2014 the destination of the outbound transfer and the exact error (timeout, connection reset, remote rejection) cannot be determined without step logs\nMEDIUM overall \u2014 the causal chain is well-supported by metrics but the final link (what specifically caused the abort) requires step log confirmation\n---\n9. Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\nAssessment\tVerdict\tReason\nInfrastructure Issue\tYES \u2014 LIKELY\tPre-step IO contention from concurrent workload, large outbound transfer stall/timeout, and rising system load are all infrastructure-layer signals. The abort was triggered by an infrastructure condition (network/IO), not a code defect.\nCode Issue\tNO \u2014 UNLIKELY\tNo compiler errors, no syntax errors. \"Aborted\" classification and exit code 2 indicate external termination. The WLAN source tree itself is not implicated.\nMixed\tPOSSIBLE\tCannot exclude a remote endpoint issue (Artifactory, SCM server) contributing to the upload failure. The remote endpoint is in the execution path but has no telemetry available.\n---\n10. Recommended Remediation\nRetrieve VerifySrc step logs from CloudBees: Access the CloudBees Commander UI for job f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f \u2192 Step \"VerifySrc\" \u2192 View Log. Identify the destination of the ~354MB outbound transfer and the exact error message (timeout, connection reset, upload failure).\nIdentify the concurrent workload causing pre-step IO contention: Check CloudBees agent configuration for san-w175-ha1-4-07 to determine how many concurrent jobs were running at 06:19:14\u201306:19:32Z. The IO await spike before the step started indicates another job was performing IO-intensive operations simultaneously.\nInvestigate the upload endpoint: Once the destination of the outbound transfer is identified from step logs, check the health and availability of that endpoint at 06:19:50\u201306:21:07Z. A slow or overloaded upload target would explain the transfer stall.\nCheck network bandwidth on san-w175-ha1-4-07: A ~354MB upload in ~45 seconds (~63 Mbps) is substantial. Verify whether the agent's network interface was saturated or whether the upload was competing with other network traffic from concurrent jobs.\nRe-run the build: If the IO contention and upload stall were transient, re-trigger the build. Monitor IO and network metrics during the re-run.\n---\n11. Preventive Actions\nConfigure Datadog Log Pipeline on san-w175-ha1-4-07: The Datadog Agent is installed but no logs are forwarded. Configure log collection for CloudBees agent logs and syslog. All 20 san-w175-ha1 hosts appear to lack log pipelines \u2014 this should be a fleet-wide remediation.\nAdd IO Wait and Network Saturation Monitors: Create Datadog monitors on system.io.await (alert >20ms) and system.net.bytes_sent (alert on sustained high outbound) for all san-w175 build agents. Pre-step IO contention would have been detectable before the build failure.\nConcurrent Job Throttling: The rising load average (0.81 \u2192 1.97) and pre-step IO contention indicate concurrent jobs competing for storage resources. Implement IO-aware job scheduling \u2014 limit concurrent IO-intensive steps on the same agent.\nUpload Retry Logic in VerifySrc: Implement retry logic with exponential backoff for the outbound transfer in the VerifySrc script. A single transient network stall should not abort the entire build.\nIncrease Upload Timeout: If the abort is triggered by a fixed timeout, consider increasing the timeout for large WLAN source tree uploads, or implement chunked transfer with progress monitoring.\nCross-Job Pattern Analysis: This is the second consecutive WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort (exit code 2, \"Aborted\") across two different agents (san-w175-ja4-6-06 and san-w175-ha1-4-07). Investigate whether the VerifySrc script has a systemic timeout or transfer issue affecting all WLAN TFH builds, or whether the remote upload endpoint is consistently slow/overloaded during this time window.\nStandardize Agent Log Forwarding: Audit all san-w175 build agents (both ha1 and ja4 racks) for Datadog log pipeline configuration. Consistent log forwarding across the fleet is essential for rapid RCA.\n---\n12. Sources Used\nSource Type\tQuery Window\tEvidence\tRelevance\nCloudBees Job Payload\tN/A (provided)\tJob ID, step \"VerifySrc\", exit code 2, agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07, failedReason \"Aborted\"\tHIGH \u2014 Primary evidence source\nDatadog Host Inventory\tCurrent\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07 confirmed with Agent 7.64.1, GNU/Linux. 20 san-w175-ha1 hosts all registered.\tHIGH \u2014 Confirms telemetry availability\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.io.await/util\t06:19:05\u201306:21:50Z\tPeak 15.97ms await / 15.97% util at ~06:19:23Z (pre-step); settled during step\tHIGH \u2014 Pre-step IO contention from concurrent workload\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.net.bytes_sent\t06:19:11\u201306:21:15Z\t~354MB outbound in 5 successive bursts during step window\tHIGH \u2014 Dominant infrastructure signal; identifies upload as primary operation\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.net.bytes_rcvd\t06:19:11\u201306:21:15Z\tOnly ~1.2\u20131.5MB received during step \u2014 no large download\tHIGH \u2014 Excludes download as primary operation; confirms upload pattern\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.load.1 / cpu.*\t06:19:11\u201306:21:15Z\tLoad 0.81\u21921.97 (concurrent workloads); CPU drop to 0.07% (abort); stolen=0 (no VM contention)\tHIGH \u2014 Confirms abort pattern and concurrent workload pressure\nDatadog Logs (Flex)\t06:16:52\u201306:26:00Z\tZero log entries \u2014 no log pipeline on san-w175-ha1-4-07\tConfirms log coverage gap\nDatadog Logs \u2014 Artifactory (Flex)\t06:19:00\u201306:22:00Z\tZero LDAP sync failures \u2014 LDAP not a factor for this job\tExplicitly excludes LDAP as contributing factor\nDatadog Incidents\t06:16:52\u201306:26:00Z\tZero active incidents\tNo relevant findings\nPrior Job RCA (san-w175-ja4-6-06)\tSame time window\tSame exit code 2, same \"Aborted\" reason, same VerifySrc step \u2014 cross-job pattern identified\tMEDIUM \u2014 Pattern correlation; suggests systemic VerifySrc issue across WLAN TFH builds",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_rca_f179cb72\",\"name\":\"RCA_f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f.txt\",\"description\":\"Root Cause Analysis Report for CloudBees job f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f, build WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2, outcome ERROR / ABORTED.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees procedure for project CRMBuilds. The failed job used this procedure.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_verify_src\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Failed CloudBees step. Step ID f179cb72-2ade-f1e2-b856-2686f9881e6f. Started at 2026-07-07 06:19:50 UTC and aborted at 2026-07-07 06:21:07 UTC with duration about 1m 17s.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_source_verification\",\"name\":\"Source verification step\",\"description\":\"The report characterizes VerifySrc as a source verification step. On this host, the step was dominated by a large outbound transfer, suggesting upload of source verification data or artifacts.\"}],\"log_symptoms\":[{\"id\":\"symptom_exit_code_2\",\"name\":\"Exit code 2\",\"description\":\"CloudBees step metadata reported failedStep.exitCode = \\\"2\\\". The report interprets this as a script-level abort or return code from a failed transfer utility.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_aborted_reason\",\"name\":\"Declared failure reason Aborted\",\"description\":\"CloudBees executionContext.failedReason = \\\"Aborted\\\", indicating the step terminated before natural completion.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_pre_step_io_contention\",\"name\":\"Pre-step IO contention\",\"description\":\"Datadog metrics showed system.io.await peaking at 15.97ms and system.io.util at 15.97% around 2026-07-07 06:19:23 UTC, about 27 seconds before VerifySrc started.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_massive_outbound_burst\",\"name\":\"Massive outbound network burst\",\"description\":\"Datadog system.net.bytes_sent showed about 354MB outbound during the step window in bursts of approximately 55MB, 40MB, 54MB, 107MB, and 98MB.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_minimal_inbound_traffic\",\"name\":\"Minimal inbound traffic\",\"description\":\"During the step, inbound traffic was only about 1.2\u20131.5MB, with no large source-fetch download pattern observed.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_rising_system_load\",\"name\":\"Rising system load\",\"description\":\"Datadog system.load.1 rose from 0.81 to 1.97 across the correlation window, consistent with accumulating concurrent process pressure.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_cpu_user_drop\",\"name\":\"Abrupt CPU user drop\",\"description\":\"Datadog system.cpu.user dropped from about 1.02% to 0.07% near the end of the step, consistent with process termination.\"}],\"system_statuses\":[{\"id\":\"status_job_completed_error\",\"name\":\"Job outcome completed_error / error\",\"description\":\"The job ended with outcome completed_error / error after the VerifySrc step aborted.\"},{\"id\":\"status_agent_metrics_available\",\"name\":\"Datadog Agent installed and reporting metrics\",\"description\":\"Agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07 is GNU/Linux with Datadog Agent 7.64.1 installed, and host metrics were available.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_cpu_stolen\",\"name\":\"CPU stolen equals zero\",\"description\":\"Datadog system.cpu.stolen was 0 throughout the correlation window, excluding hypervisor CPU theft as a contributing factor.\"},{\"id\":\"status_memory_disk_healthy\",\"name\":\"Memory and disk not exhausted\",\"description\":\"Memory was reported as 392\u2013393GB usable and disk usage as 42.1%, so memory pressure and disk exhaustion were excluded by the report.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_active_incidents\",\"name\":\"Zero active incidents\",\"description\":\"Datadog incidents showed zero active incidents during the job execution window.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_artifactory_ldap_errors\",\"name\":\"Zero Artifactory LDAP failures\",\"description\":\"Datadog logs for Artifactory showed zero LDAP sync failures during the job window; LDAP was excluded as a contributing factor.\"}],\"root_causes\":[{\"id\":\"root_cause_outbound_transfer_timeout_under_io_pressure\",\"name\":\"Probable outbound transfer timeout or abort under pre-existing IO pressure\",\"description\":\"The report identifies the probable root cause as the VerifySrc step initiating a large outbound transfer of about 354MB while the agent storage subsystem was already under IO contention from a concurrent workload. The upload may have stalled, timed out, or been rejected/dropped by the remote endpoint; VerifySrc then exited with code 2 and CloudBees classified the step as Aborted.\"}],\"data_gaps\":[{\"id\":\"gap_no_datadog_log_pipeline\",\"name\":\"No application-level logs forwarded to Datadog\",\"description\":\"The Datadog Agent was installed and reporting metrics, but no log pipeline was configured for san-w175-ha1-4-07, resulting in zero log entries from the host.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_step_stdout_stderr_missing\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc stdout/stderr not available in supplied evidence\",\"description\":\"The report states that step-level stdout/stderr must be retrieved directly from CloudBees to confirm the exact abort trigger.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_unknown_outbound_destination\",\"name\":\"Destination of outbound transfer unknown\",\"description\":\"The remote endpoint receiving the approximately 354MB outbound transfer could not be identified from available metadata. Candidate endpoint types mentioned were Artifactory, SCM, or build coordination server, but no specific endpoint was evidenced.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_exact_abort_trigger_unknown\",\"name\":\"Exact abort trigger unknown\",\"description\":\"The report could not determine whether the final abort was caused by timeout, connection reset, remote rejection, or another transfer failure without step logs.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_concurrent_workload_identity_unknown\",\"name\":\"Concurrent workload identity unknown\",\"description\":\"Rising load and pre-step IO contention suggested at least one other concurrent process or job, but the specific workload was not identified in the supplied evidence.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_commander_host_not_identified\",\"name\":\"Commander host not identified\",\"description\":\"No Commander host was identified in job metadata, and there was no evidence of Commander contribution to the failure.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_remote_endpoint_telemetry_unavailable\",\"name\":\"Remote upload endpoint telemetry unavailable\",\"description\":\"The remote endpoint was in the execution path, but endpoint identity and telemetry were unavailable in the supplied evidence.\"}],\"preventive_actions\":[{\"id\":\"prevent_configure_datadog_log_pipeline\",\"name\":\"Configure Datadog log pipeline\",\"description\":\"Configure log collection for CloudBees agent logs and syslog on san-w175-ha1-4-07. The report recommends fleet-wide remediation for all san-w175-ha1 hosts that lack log pipelines.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_add_io_network_monitors\",\"name\":\"Add IO wait and network saturation monitors\",\"description\":\"Create Datadog monitors for system.io.await, alerting above 20ms, and system.net.bytes_sent for sustained high outbound traffic across san-w175 build agents.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_concurrent_job_throttling\",\"name\":\"Concurrent job throttling\",\"description\":\"Implement IO-aware job scheduling and limit concurrent IO-intensive steps on the same agent to reduce storage contention.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_upload_retry_logic\",\"name\":\"Add upload retry logic in VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Implement retry logic with exponential backoff for the outbound transfer in the VerifySrc script so a transient network stall does not abort the entire build.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_increase_upload_timeout\",\"name\":\"Increase or improve upload timeout behavior\",\"description\":\"If the abort is caused by a fixed timeout, increase the timeout for large WLAN source tree uploads or implement chunked transfer with progress monitoring.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_cross_job_pattern_analysis\",\"name\":\"Perform cross-job pattern analysis\",\"description\":\"Investigate whether VerifySrc has a systemic timeout or transfer issue across WLAN TFH builds, because this was reported as the second consecutive WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort with exit code 2 and failure reason Aborted across different agents.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_standardize_agent_log_forwarding\",\"name\":\"Standardize agent log forwarding\",\"description\":\"Audit san-w175 build agents across ha1 and ja4 racks for Datadog log pipeline configuration and standardize log forwarding across the fleet.\"}],\"remediations\":[{\"id\":\"remed_retrieve_verifysrc_logs\",\"name\":\"Retrieve VerifySrc step logs from CloudBees\",\"description\":\"Use the CloudBees Commander UI for job f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f, open Step VerifySrc, and view the log to identify the outbound transfer destination and exact error message.\"},{\"id\":\"remed_identify_concurrent_workload\",\"name\":\"Identify concurrent workload causing IO contention\",\"description\":\"Check CloudBees agent configuration and job activity on san-w175-ha1-4-07 around 2026-07-07 06:19:14\u201306:19:32 UTC to determine whether other jobs were running IO-intensive operations.\"},{\"id\":\"remed_investigate_upload_endpoint\",\"name\":\"Investigate upload endpoint\",\"description\":\"After identifying the outbound transfer destination from step logs, check health and availability of that endpoint during 2026-07-07 06:19:50\u201306:21:07 UTC.\"},{\"id\":\"remed_check_network_bandwidth\",\"name\":\"Check network bandwidth on san-w175-ha1-4-07\",\"description\":\"Verify whether the agent network interface was saturated or competing with traffic from concurrent jobs during the approximately 354MB upload in about 45 seconds.\"},{\"id\":\"remed_rerun_build\",\"name\":\"Re-run the build\",\"description\":\"If IO contention and upload stall were transient, re-trigger the build and monitor IO and network metrics during the re-run.\"}],\"annotations\":[{\"id\":\"annotation_job_context\",\"name\":\"Job context\",\"description\":\"Job ID f179cb72-2009-f120-bf77-2686f9881e6f; job name WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2_20260706_231638_231652; project CRMBuilds; agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07; build type WLAN TFH 3.6.c2 QCATFSWPZ variant.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_timeline\",\"name\":\"Build timeline summary\",\"description\":\"Job started at 2026-07-07 06:16:52 UTC. VerifySrc started at 06:19:50 UTC. VerifySrc aborted at 06:21:07 UTC. Job ended at 06:25:54 UTC.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_confidence_medium\",\"name\":\"Overall confidence MEDIUM\",\"description\":\"The report assigns MEDIUM overall confidence: abort, outbound transfer, and pre-step IO contention are high-confidence findings, while the exact abort trigger requires step log confirmation.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_infrastructure_likely\",\"name\":\"Infrastructure issue likely; code issue unlikely\",\"description\":\"The report assesses infrastructure issue as likely due to IO contention, outbound transfer stall/timeout, and rising load. It assesses code defect as unlikely because no compiler or syntax errors were evidenced.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_prior_job_pattern\",\"name\":\"Prior job pattern correlation\",\"description\":\"The report notes a prior WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort on san-w175-ja4-6-06 with the same step name, exit code 2, failure reason Aborted, and procedure, but with a different infrastructure signature.\"}],\"relationships\":[{\"id\":\"rel_procedure_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Procedure was extracted from the RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179cb72\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Step was extracted from the RCA log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verify_src\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_f179cb72\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_class_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Step class was extracted from the RCA log.\",\"source_id\"