    "file_name": "RCA_179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010.txt",
    "log_text": "Root Cause Analysis Report\nJob ID: f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010  |  Build: WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1  |  Outcome: ERROR / ABORTED\n\n---\n1. Executive Summary\nCloudBees job f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010 failed during the \"VerifySrc\" step with exit code 2 on agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07. The CloudBees execution context classifies the failure reason as \"Aborted\".\n\nThis job is critically significant for three reasons:\n\nSame host as job f179cb72 \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07 has now failed twice with identical signatures: exit code 2, \"Aborted\", VerifySrc, Build.Rel.602829, WLAN TFH QCATFSWPZ. This is the third consecutive WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort across the five-job session (also including f179cb7a on san-w175-ja4-6-06).\nEarlier time window \u2014 this job ran at 06:08:59\u201306:18:16Z, approximately 11 minutes before job f179cb72 (06:16:52\u201306:25:54Z) on the same host. The host failed VerifySrc twice in the same morning session.\nIdentical infrastructure signature \u2014 large outbound transfer (~70MB+ sent) during/around the step, CPU dropping to near zero before step starts, IO near zero during step, no LDAP failures. The pattern is a precise match to the previous job on this host.\nProbable Root Cause: The VerifySrc step was aborted during a large outbound transfer (~70MB+ sent starting 18 seconds before the step formally began). The transfer stalled or exceeded a timeout threshold, triggering an abort. This is the same failure mode as job f179cb72 on the same host, confirming a persistent, recurring issue with the VerifySrc upload operation on san-w175-ha1-4-07 \u2014 not a transient one-time event.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f No application-level logs are forwarded from san-w175-ha1-4-07 to Datadog. The Datadog Agent is installed and reporting metrics, but no log pipeline is configured. Step-level stdout/stderr must be retrieved directly from CloudBees.\n\n---\n2. Job Context\nJob ID: f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010\nJob Name: WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1_20260706_230844_230859\nProject: CRMBuilds\nProcedure: Build.Rel.602829\nOutcome: completed_error / error\nFailed Step: VerifySrc (Step ID: f179ca58-867f-f12f-be4a-1ea035bf3243)\nExit Code: 2 \u2014 script-level abort\nAgent Host: san-w175-ha1-4-07 (GNU/Linux, Datadog Agent 7.64.1 \u2705 \u2014 same host as job f179cb72)\nBuild Name: WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1\nDeclared Failure Reason: Aborted\nBuild Type: WLAN TFH 3.7.1 \u2014 QCATFSWPZ-1 variant (note: f179cb72 was QCATFSWPZ-2, same base build)\nStep Duration: ~58 seconds (06:11:47 \u2192 06:12:46Z)\nJob Duration: ~9m 17s (06:08:59 \u2192 06:18:16Z)\nDisk Usage at Step Time: 5.13% \u2014 significantly lower than the later job's 42.1% on the same host\n---\n3. Build Timeline\nTime (UTC)\tEvent\tDetail\n2026-07-07 06:08:59\tJob Started\tCRMBuilds / Build.Rel.602829 initiated on san-w175-ha1-4-07\n~2026-07-07 06:09:28\u201306:09:52Z\tLarge Inbound Burst (Pre-Step)\tnet_rcvd spikes: 2.05MB \u2192 16.93MB \u2192 50.81MB \u2192 49.69MB \u2192 29.03MB \u2014 ~148MB total inbound. Large source package download during job setup phase. CPU user peaks at 1.48%.\n~2026-07-07 06:10:22\u201306:11:41Z\t\u26a1 Large Outbound Burst Begins (Pre-Step)\tnet_sent: 11.52MB \u2192 5.47MB \u2192 10.35MB \u2014 sustained outbound transfer begins ~1m 25s before step starts. CPU drops to 0.05% at ~06:11:20Z.\n~2026-07-07 06:11:05Z\tIO Spike (Pre-Step)\tIO await 2.128ms, IO util 3.464% \u2014 brief storage burst from download write. Subsides quickly.\n2026-07-07 06:11:47\tVerifySrc Step Started\tStep begins \u2014 Correlation Window Opens. Outbound transfer already in progress (7.08MB/6s). CPU at 0.05%. Load declining from 1.71 \u2192 1.15.\n06:11:47\u201306:12:46Z\t\u26a1 Sustained Outbound During Step\tnet_sent: 7.08MB \u2192 382KB \u2192 4.51MB \u2192 17.67MB \u2192 18.11MB \u2014 outbound burst continues and intensifies during step. IO near zero. CPU 0.05\u20130.19%.\n2026-07-07 06:12:46\tVerifySrc Step ABORTED\tExit Code 2 \u2014 step terminated \u2014 Correlation Window Closes (duration: ~58s)\n2026-07-07 06:18:16\tJob Ended\tJob terminates with outcome: error (~5m 30s after step abort \u2014 extended cleanup/teardown)\n~2026-07-07 06:16:52Z\t\u26a1 Second Job Starts on Same Host\tJob f179cb72 (WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2) starts on san-w175-ha1-4-07 while this job is still in teardown \u2014 overlapping execution on same agent\n---\n4. Execution Path Inventory\nFailed Step: \"VerifySrc\" \u2014 source verification step; large inbound download (~148MB) during setup, then large outbound transfer (~70MB+) during/around step execution\nAgent Host: san-w175-ha1-4-07 (GNU/Linux, Datadog Agent 7.64.1 \u2014 metrics available, no log pipeline; same host as job f179cb72)\nCommander Host: Not identified \u2014 no evidence of Commander contribution to failure\nInvoked Services: Source repository (large inbound ~148MB download during setup); remote upload endpoint (large outbound ~70MB+ during step \u2014 same unknown endpoint as job f179cb72)\nConcurrent Job Overlap: Job f179cb72 started on this same host at 06:16:52Z while this job was still in teardown (ended 06:18:16Z) \u2014 confirmed overlapping execution\n---\n5. Detected Error Codes & Signals\nCode / Signal\tSource\tMeaning\tEvidence\nExit Code 2\tCloudBees Step Metadata\tScript-level abort \u2014 timeout or transfer failure. Identical to jobs f179cb7a and f179cb72.\tfailedStep.exitCode = \"2\"\nAborted\tCloudBees executionContext\tStep terminated before natural completion\texecutionContext.failedReason = \"Aborted\"\nLarge Inbound ~148MB (Pre-Step)\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\t50.81MB + 49.69MB + 29.03MB + smaller bursts at ~06:09:28\u201306:11:05Z \u2014 large source package download during job setup. Larger than previous job's pre-step activity.\tsystem.net.bytes_rcvd peaks at points 7\u20139 of first metric window\nSustained Outbound ~70MB+ (During/Around Step)\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\t11.52MB + 5.47MB + 10.35MB (pre-step) + 7.08MB + 4.51MB + 17.67MB + 18.11MB (during step) = ~74MB total outbound. Sustained upload operation that was already in progress when step started.\tsystem.net.bytes_sent sustained across both metric windows\nIO Spike 2.128ms (Pre-Step)\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tBrief IO await spike at 06:11:17Z from download write. Subsides to near zero before step starts. IO is NOT a factor during the step itself.\tsystem.io.await = 2.128ms at point 3 of second window\nCPU Drop to 0.05% Pre-Step\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tCPU user drops from ~1.10% to 0.05% at ~06:11:20Z \u2014 27 seconds before step starts. Prior process completed. Step runs on an idle CPU.\tsystem.cpu.user sharp decline at points 9\u201312 of second CPU window\nDisk 5.13% Used\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tDisk nearly empty at this time. Contrast: same host showed 42.1% disk usage during job f179cb72 (~11 minutes later). Disk fill-up between the two jobs is notable but not a factor for this job.\tsystem.disk.in_use = 0.0513 (5.13%)\nCPU Stolen = 0\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tNo hypervisor CPU theft \u2014 VM-level resource contention excluded\tsystem.cpu.stolen = 0 throughout\nNo Artifactory LDAP Failures\tDatadog Logs (Flex)\tZero LDAP sync failures during 06:08:00\u201306:15:00Z \u2014 LDAP is NOT a factor\tZero results for Artifactory LDAP queries\n\u26a0\ufe0f Disk Jump: 5.13% \u2192 42.1%\tDatadog Metrics \u2014 san-w175-ha1-4-07\tDisk usage on san-w175-ha1-4-07 jumped from 5.13% (this job, 06:11Z) to 42.1% (job f179cb72, 06:19Z) \u2014 a ~37% increase in ~8 minutes. The large inbound download (~148MB) and subsequent jobs likely filled the workspace. This is a secondary finding \u2014 not a cause of this job's failure but a risk factor for subsequent jobs.\tCross-job metric comparison: this job vs f179cb72 on same host\n---\n6. Correlated Observations\nCloudBees\nStep \"VerifySrc\" failed with exit code 2 and failure reason \"Aborted\" \u2014 identical to jobs f179cb7a (san-w175-ja4-6-06) and f179cb72 (same host, later)\nStep duration: ~58 seconds \u2014 same as the Balsam job (f179cb71), shorter than f179cb72's 77s\nBuild name: WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1 \u2014 this is variant \"-1\" of the same build that also failed as variant \"-2\" (job f179cb7a on san-w175-ja4-6-06). Both variants of the same WLAN TFH 3.7.1-01029 build failed VerifySrc with exit code 2 and \"Aborted\".\nConfidence: HIGH \u2014 directly from job payload\nAgent Host (san-w175-ha1-4-07) \u2014 KEY FINDINGS\n\u2705 Datadog Agent 7.64.1 installed \u2014 full metric telemetry available\n\nLarge inbound download (~148MB) at ~06:09:28\u201306:11:05Z \u2014 source package fetch during job setup. Larger than the previous job's pre-step activity.\nSustained outbound transfer (~74MB total) starting at ~06:10:22Z \u2014 1m 25s before step starts \u2014 and continuing through the step window. The upload was already in progress when VerifySrc formally began.\nIO near zero during step \u2014 IO await 0.021\u20130.142ms, IO util 0.091\u20130.411%. Storage is not a bottleneck.\nCPU at 0.05% during step \u2014 host is idle from a compute perspective.\nLoad declining from 1.71 \u2192 1.15 during step \u2014 pressure was higher before the step and was already subsiding.\nMemory: ~392\u2013393GB usable \u2014 no memory pressure.\nDisk: 5.13% used \u2014 nearly empty at this time. The disk fills to 42.1% by the next job (~8 minutes later), suggesting the large download and workspace files from this job consumed significant disk space.\nComparison: This Job vs Previous Job on Same Host (f179cb72):\n\nSignal\tf179ca58 (this job, 06:11:47Z)\tf179cb72 (later job, 06:19:50Z)\nExit code\t2\t2\nFailure reason\tAborted\tAborted\nInbound (pre-step)\t~148MB (large download)\t~1.4MB (minimal)\nOutbound (during/around step)\t~74MB (sustained upload)\t~354MB (larger upload)\nIO await peak\t2.128ms (pre-step only)\t15.97ms (pre-step only)\nDisk usage\t5.13% (nearly empty)\t42.1% (filled by prior jobs)\nStep duration\t~58s\t~77s\nLDAP failures\tNone\tNone\nCommander Host\nNo Commander host identified \u2014 OUT_OF_SCOPE\nDatadog \u2014 Logs & Incidents\nZero log entries from san-w175-ha1-4-07 \u2014 no log pipeline configured\nZero Artifactory LDAP errors during this job's window \u2014 LDAP excluded\nZero active incidents during the job execution window\nCross-Job Pattern \u2014 WLAN TFH VerifySrc Abort (Now 3 Jobs)\n\ud83d\udd34 SYSTEMIC PATTERN CONFIRMED: Three WLAN TFH VerifySrc aborts with identical signatures:\n\nJob f179cb7a \u2014 WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-2 on san-w175-ja4-6-06 (06:19:31Z)\nJob f179cb72 \u2014 WLAN.TFH.3.6.c2-00721-QCATFSWPZ-2 on san-w175-ha1-4-07 (06:19:50Z)\nJob f179ca58 \u2014 WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1 on san-w175-ha1-4-07 (06:11:47Z)\nThree different build variants, two different agents, same rack (san-w175), same procedure, same exit code 2, same \"Aborted\" reason, same VerifySrc step, all with large outbound transfers. This is not an agent-specific issue \u2014 it is a systemic VerifySrc script or remote endpoint issue affecting all WLAN TFH builds.\n---\n7. Probable Root Cause\nPrimary: Systemic VerifySrc Upload Abort \u2014 Remote Endpoint Failure or Script Timeout\n\nThe VerifySrc step initiated a large outbound transfer (~74MB) to a remote endpoint, beginning ~1m 25s before the step formally started. The transfer stalled or exceeded a timeout threshold during the step window, triggering an abort (exit code 2). This is the same failure mode as jobs f179cb7a and f179cb72, confirmed across three different WLAN TFH build variants on two different agents. The consistent pattern across multiple agents and build variants eliminates agent-specific infrastructure as the root cause and points to a systemic issue with the VerifySrc upload operation \u2014 either the remote endpoint was unavailable/slow, or the VerifySrc script has a timeout that is too short for the volume of data being transferred.\n\nCausal Chain:\n\nJob setup phase downloads large source package (~148MB inbound at ~06:09:28\u201306:11:05Z)\nVerifySrc begins uploading verification data/artifacts to remote endpoint at ~06:10:22Z (1m 25s before step formally starts)\nVerifySrc step formally starts at 06:11:47Z \u2014 upload already in progress (~74MB sent so far)\nUpload continues during step (7.08MB \u2192 4.51MB \u2192 17.67MB \u2192 18.11MB per 6s interval)\nTransfer stalls or exceeds timeout threshold \u2014 abort signal triggered\nVerifySrc script exits with code 2 at 06:12:46Z\nCloudBees marks step as failed with reason \"Aborted\"\nSupporting Evidence:\n\n~74MB outbound transfer during/around step (Datadog system.net.bytes_sent)\nTransfer already in progress 1m 25s before step starts \u2014 upload is a pre-step operation that continues into the step (Datadog metrics)\nIO near zero during step \u2014 storage not a bottleneck (Datadog system.io.await)\nCPU at 0.05% during step \u2014 compute not a bottleneck (Datadog system.cpu.user)\nExit code 2 + \"Aborted\" \u2014 external termination confirmed (CloudBees metadata)\nCPU stolen = 0% \u2014 hypervisor contention excluded (Datadog system.cpu.stolen)\nNo LDAP failures \u2014 authorization excluded (Datadog logs)\nSame failure on same host 11 minutes later (job f179cb72) \u2014 persistent, not transient (cross-job analysis)\nSame failure on different agent (f179cb7a on san-w175-ja4-6-06) \u2014 not host-specific (cross-job analysis)\n---\n8. Confidence Level\n\u2705 HIGH (for systemic pattern) / MEDIUM (for specific abort trigger)\n\nHIGH confidence that this is a systemic VerifySrc issue \u2014 three identical failures across two agents and three build variants confirm this is not agent-specific\nHIGH confidence that the step was aborted during an outbound transfer \u2014 direct metric evidence\nHIGH confidence that agent infrastructure is not the root cause \u2014 IO near zero, CPU near zero, no memory/disk pressure during step\nMEDIUM confidence on the specific abort trigger (remote endpoint failure vs. script timeout) \u2014 step logs required to confirm\n---\n9. Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\nAssessment\tVerdict\tReason\nInfrastructure Issue (Agent)\tNO \u2014 EXCLUDED\tIO near zero, CPU 0.05%, no memory/disk pressure during step. Same failure occurs on a different agent (san-w175-ja4-6-06). Agent infrastructure is not the cause.\nInfrastructure Issue (Remote Endpoint)\tLIKELY \u2014 YES\tThe remote endpoint receiving the outbound transfer is in the execution path and is the most likely point of failure. Three jobs failing with the same upload abort pattern across different agents strongly suggests the remote endpoint was unavailable, slow, or rejecting connections during this time window.\nCode Issue (Script)\tPOSSIBLE\tThe VerifySrc script may have an insufficient timeout for large WLAN TFH source trees. Cannot confirm without step logs.\nMixed\tPOSSIBLE\tRemote endpoint failure + insufficient script timeout could both contribute.\n---\n10. Recommended Remediation\nIdentify the remote upload endpoint from VerifySrc step logs: This is the single highest-priority action. Retrieve step logs for all three WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort jobs (f179ca58, f179cb7a, f179cb72) and identify the common upload destination. Check the health and availability of that endpoint during 06:10\u201306:21Z on 2026-07-07.\nInvestigate disk fill-up on san-w175-ha1-4-07: Disk usage jumped from 5.13% to 42.1% between this job (06:11Z) and the next job (06:19Z) on the same host. The ~148MB inbound download and workspace files from this job likely contributed. Verify that workspace cleanup is occurring between jobs and that disk usage is not trending toward exhaustion.\nCheck for overlapping job execution: Job f179cb72 started at 06:16:52Z while this job was still in teardown (ended 06:18:16Z). Verify whether CloudBees is allowing concurrent jobs on san-w175-ha1-4-07 and whether this overlap contributed to the disk fill-up and the second job's failure.\nRe-run all three WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort jobs after confirming the remote endpoint is healthy. If the endpoint was temporarily unavailable, re-runs should succeed.\nImplement retry logic in VerifySrc: Add retry with exponential backoff for the upload operation. A single transient endpoint failure should not abort the entire build.\n---\n11. Preventive Actions\nConfigure Datadog Log Pipeline on san-w175-ha1-4-07: This host has failed VerifySrc twice in 11 minutes. Without log forwarding, each failure requires manual CloudBees log retrieval. Immediate priority.\nMonitor the VerifySrc Upload Endpoint: Create a Datadog Synthetic test or monitor on the remote endpoint that VerifySrc uploads to. Alert immediately when the endpoint becomes unavailable \u2014 this would have detected the issue before any of the three WLAN TFH jobs failed.\nDisk Usage Monitoring on san-w175-ha1-4-07: The 5.13% \u2192 42.1% disk jump in 8 minutes is alarming. Create a Datadog monitor on system.disk.in_use for all san-w175 agents. Alert at 70% to prevent disk exhaustion from causing future build failures.\nWorkspace Cleanup Policy: Enforce CloudBees workspace cleanup between jobs on san-w175-ha1-4-07. The rapid disk fill-up suggests workspaces from failed jobs are not being cleaned up, which will eventually cause disk exhaustion.\nConcurrent Job Limit: Investigate whether san-w175-ha1-4-07 should allow concurrent jobs given the disk fill-up pattern. The overlap between f179ca58 (teardown) and f179cb72 (startup) at 06:16:52Z may be contributing to resource contention.\nVerifySrc Timeout Increase: Increase the upload timeout in the VerifySrc script for WLAN TFH builds, which involve large source trees (148MB+ downloads, 74\u2013354MB uploads).\n---\n12. Sources Used\nSource Type\tQuery Window\tEvidence\tRelevance\nCloudBees Job Payload\tN/A (provided)\tJob ID, step \"VerifySrc\", exit code 2, agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07, failedReason \"Aborted\"\tHIGH \u2014 Primary evidence source\nDatadog Host Inventory\tCurrent\tsan-w175-ha1-4-07 confirmed Agent 7.64.1, GNU/Linux \u2014 same host as job f179cb72\tHIGH \u2014 Confirms telemetry availability and host identity\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.net.bytes_rcvd/sent\t06:09:04\u201306:13:00Z\t~148MB inbound (pre-step download); ~74MB outbound (during/around step upload)\tHIGH \u2014 Identifies upload as primary operation and abort trigger\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.io.await/util\t06:09:04\u201306:13:00Z\tPeak 2.128ms pre-step; near zero during step \u2014 IO not a factor\tHIGH \u2014 Excludes IO contention as cause\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.cpu.user/stolen/load\t06:09:12\u201306:13:00Z\tCPU 0.05% during step; stolen 0%; load declining 1.71\u21921.15\tHIGH \u2014 Excludes CPU/compute as cause\nDatadog Metrics \u2014 system.disk.in_use\t06:11:04\u201306:13:00Z\t5.13% at step time; cross-job comparison shows 42.1% on same host 8 minutes later\tMEDIUM \u2014 Disk fill-up pattern identified; secondary finding\nDatadog Logs \u2014 Artifactory (Flex)\t06:08:00\u201306:15:00Z\tZero LDAP failures \u2014 authorization excluded\tHIGH \u2014 Explicitly excludes LDAP as factor\nDatadog Incidents\t06:08:00\u201306:20:00Z\tZero active incidents\tNo relevant findings\nCross-Job Analysis (f179cb7a, f179cb72)\tSame morning session\tThree WLAN TFH VerifySrc aborts: exit 2, Aborted, Build.Rel.602829 \u2014 two agents, three build variants\tHIGH \u2014 Confirms systemic pattern, eliminates agent-specific cause",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\",\"name\":\"RCA_179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010.txt\",\"description\":\"Root Cause Analysis Report for CloudBees job f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010, build WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1, outcome ERROR / ABORTED.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees procedure for CRMBuilds job f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010. The failed step in this procedure was VerifySrc.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Failed CloudBees step. Step ID f179ca58-867f-f12f-be4a-1ea035bf3243. Ran on agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07 from approximately 2026-07-07 06:11:47Z to 06:12:46Z and terminated with exit code 2 and failed reason Aborted.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_source_verification\",\"name\":\"Source verification step\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc is described as a source verification step involving a large source package download during setup and a large outbound transfer during or around step execution.\"}],\"log_symptoms\":[{\"id\":\"symptom_job_error_aborted\",\"name\":\"CloudBees job completed_error / error with Aborted classification\",\"description\":\"Job f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010 failed with outcome completed_error / error and CloudBees execution context failedReason Aborted.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_verifysrc_exit_code_2\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc failed with exit code 2\",\"description\":\"CloudBees step metadata reports failedStep.exitCode = \\\"2\\\" for VerifySrc, interpreted in the RCA as a script-level abort.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_large_inbound_prestep\",\"name\":\"Large inbound transfer before VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Datadog metrics show approximately 148MB inbound during job setup around 2026-07-07 06:09:28Z to 06:11:05Z, described as a large source package download.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_sustained_outbound_transfer\",\"name\":\"Sustained outbound transfer during and around VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Datadog metrics show approximately 74MB total outbound transfer starting before VerifySrc and continuing through the step window, including pre-step and during-step system.net.bytes_sent bursts.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_abort_during_outbound_transfer\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc aborted during outbound transfer window\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc started at 06:11:47Z while outbound transfer was already in progress and aborted at 06:12:46Z after sustained outbound activity during the step.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_cross_job_pattern\",\"name\":\"Recurring WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort pattern\",\"description\":\"The RCA reports three WLAN TFH VerifySrc aborts with the same signatures: exit code 2, failed reason Aborted, procedure Build.Rel.602829, and large outbound transfers across jobs f179ca58, f179cb7a, and f179cb72 on two agents.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_same_host_repeat\",\"name\":\"Same host repeated VerifySrc abort\",\"description\":\"Agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07 failed VerifySrc for this job and later job f179cb72 with identical signature on the same morning session.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_disk_usage_jump_secondary\",\"name\":\"Disk usage jump after this job\",\"description\":\"Datadog metrics show disk usage on san-w175-ha1-4-07 was 5.13% at this job's step time and 42.1% during later job f179cb72, a reported increase of approximately 37% in about 8 minutes. The RCA treats this as a secondary risk, not the cause of this job's failure.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_overlapping_job_execution\",\"name\":\"Overlapping execution on same agent\",\"description\":\"Job f179cb72 reportedly started on san-w175-ha1-4-07 at 06:16:52Z while this job was still in teardown and before this job ended at 06:18:16Z.\"}],\"system_statuses\":[{\"id\":\"status_agent_metrics_available\",\"name\":\"Datadog Agent installed and metrics available\",\"description\":\"Agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07 is GNU/Linux with Datadog Agent 7.64.1 installed and reporting metrics.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_datadog_log_pipeline\",\"name\":\"No Datadog application log pipeline configured\",\"description\":\"The RCA states no application-level logs are forwarded from san-w175-ha1-4-07 to Datadog, although the Datadog Agent reports metrics.\"},{\"id\":\"status_cpu_not_bottleneck\",\"name\":\"CPU not a bottleneck during VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Datadog metrics show CPU user approximately 0.05% during the step and CPU stolen = 0 throughout, excluding CPU and hypervisor contention as causes according to the RCA.\"},{\"id\":\"status_io_not_bottleneck\",\"name\":\"IO not a bottleneck during VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"The RCA reports IO was near zero during the VerifySrc step, with IO await approximately 0.021\u20130.142ms and IO util approximately 0.091\u20130.411%.\"},{\"id\":\"status_disk_not_cause_for_this_job\",\"name\":\"Disk usage low during failed step\",\"description\":\"Disk usage at this job's step time was reported as 5.13%, and the RCA states disk was not a factor for this job.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_memory_pressure\",\"name\":\"No memory pressure reported\",\"description\":\"The RCA reports approximately 392\u2013393GB usable memory and no memory pressure during the relevant window.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_ldap_failures\",\"name\":\"No Artifactory LDAP failures\",\"description\":\"Datadog Logs queries for 06:08:00\u201306:15:00Z returned zero Artifactory LDAP sync failures; the RCA excludes LDAP as a factor.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_active_incidents\",\"name\":\"No active Datadog incidents\",\"description\":\"Datadog Incidents query for 06:08:00\u201306:20:00Z returned zero active incidents.\"},{\"id\":\"status_commander_out_of_scope\",\"name\":\"Commander host not implicated by evidence\",\"description\":\"The RCA states no Commander host was identified and there is no evidence of Commander contribution to the failure.\"}],\"root_causes\":[{\"id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\",\"name\":\"Probable systemic VerifySrc upload abort: remote endpoint failure or script timeout\",\"description\":\"The RCA identifies the probable root cause as a systemic VerifySrc upload operation issue. A sustained outbound transfer of approximately 74MB began before VerifySrc formally started and continued during the step, after which VerifySrc aborted with exit code 2. The same pattern across multiple WLAN TFH jobs and two agents points to either an unavailable or slow remote upload endpoint, or a VerifySrc script timeout that is too short for the data volume. The exact trigger is not confirmed without step logs.\"}],\"data_gaps\":[{\"id\":\"gap_step_stdout_stderr_missing\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc stdout/stderr not available in Datadog\",\"description\":\"No application-level logs are forwarded from san-w175-ha1-4-07 to Datadog. Step-level stdout/stderr must be retrieved directly from CloudBees to confirm the upload destination and exact abort message.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_remote_upload_endpoint_unknown\",\"name\":\"Remote upload endpoint not identified\",\"description\":\"The RCA refers to a remote upload endpoint involved in the outbound VerifySrc transfer, but the endpoint identity is unknown from the available evidence.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_specific_abort_trigger_unconfirmed\",\"name\":\"Specific abort trigger unconfirmed\",\"description\":\"The RCA has medium confidence on the specific abort trigger because available evidence does not distinguish conclusively between remote endpoint failure, remote slowness, connection rejection, or an insufficient VerifySrc timeout.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_commander_host_not_identified\",\"name\":\"Commander host not identified\",\"description\":\"The Commander host is not identified in the RCA, and no evidence ties a Commander component to this failure.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_script_behavior_unconfirmed\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc script timeout behavior not confirmed\",\"description\":\"The RCA states the VerifySrc script may have an insufficient timeout, but this cannot be confirmed without the step logs or script-level evidence.\"}],\"preventive_actions\":[{\"id\":\"prevent_configure_datadog_log_pipeline\",\"name\":\"Configure Datadog log pipeline on san-w175-ha1-4-07\",\"description\":\"Configure forwarding of application and build logs from san-w175-ha1-4-07 to Datadog so future VerifySrc failures do not require manual CloudBees log retrieval.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_monitor_verifysrc_upload_endpoint\",\"name\":\"Monitor the VerifySrc upload endpoint\",\"description\":\"Create a Datadog Synthetic test or monitor for the remote endpoint used by VerifySrc uploads and alert when unavailable.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_disk_usage_monitoring\",\"name\":\"Add disk usage monitoring for san-w175 agents\",\"description\":\"Create a Datadog monitor on system.disk.in_use for all san-w175 agents, with alerting at 70%, to reduce the risk of disk exhaustion.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_workspace_cleanup_policy\",\"name\":\"Enforce workspace cleanup between jobs\",\"description\":\"Enforce CloudBees workspace cleanup between jobs on san-w175-ha1-4-07 because rapid disk fill-up suggests failed-job workspaces may not be cleaned.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_concurrent_job_limit_review\",\"name\":\"Review concurrent job limit on san-w175-ha1-4-07\",\"description\":\"Investigate whether san-w175-ha1-4-07 should allow concurrent jobs, given the reported overlap between this job's teardown and the next job's startup.\"},{\"id\":\"prevent_verifysrc_timeout_increase\",\"name\":\"Increase VerifySrc upload timeout for WLAN TFH builds\",\"description\":\"Increase the VerifySrc upload timeout for WLAN TFH builds, which involve large source trees and reported uploads in the 74\u2013354MB range.\"}],\"remediations\":[{\"id\":\"remediate_retrieve_step_logs_and_identify_endpoint\",\"name\":\"Retrieve VerifySrc step logs and identify remote endpoint\",\"description\":\"Retrieve step logs for the WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort jobs f179ca58, f179cb7a, and f179cb72, identify the common upload destination, and check its health and availability during 06:10\u201306:21Z on 2026-07-07.\"},{\"id\":\"remediate_investigate_disk_fillup\",\"name\":\"Investigate disk fill-up on san-w175-ha1-4-07\",\"description\":\"Investigate why disk usage increased from 5.13% to 42.1% between this job and later job f179cb72, and verify workspace cleanup behavior.\"},{\"id\":\"remediate_check_overlapping_execution\",\"name\":\"Check overlapping job execution on san-w175-ha1-4-07\",\"description\":\"Verify whether CloudBees allowed concurrent jobs on san-w175-ha1-4-07 and whether overlap contributed to disk fill-up or later failures.\"},{\"id\":\"remediate_rerun_wlan_tfh_jobs\",\"name\":\"Re-run affected WLAN TFH VerifySrc jobs\",\"description\":\"After confirming the remote endpoint is healthy, re-run the three WLAN TFH VerifySrc abort jobs to determine whether they succeed.\"},{\"id\":\"remediate_add_verifysrc_retry_logic\",\"name\":\"Add retry logic to VerifySrc upload\",\"description\":\"Implement retry with exponential backoff for the VerifySrc upload operation so a single transient endpoint failure does not abort the entire build.\"}],\"annotations\":[{\"id\":\"annotation_job_context\",\"name\":\"Job context\",\"description\":\"Job ID f179ca58-7a71-f11a-8dc3-4efb9ff91010; job name WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1_20260706_230844_230859; project CRMBuilds; procedure Build.Rel.602829; agent host san-w175-ha1-4-07; build WLAN.TFH.3.7.1-01029-QCATFSWPZ-1; job duration approximately 06:08:59\u201306:18:16Z.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_timeline\",\"name\":\"Failure timeline\",\"description\":\"Job started at 2026-07-07 06:08:59Z. Large inbound burst occurred around 06:09:28\u201306:09:52Z. Large outbound transfer began around 06:10:22\u201306:11:41Z. VerifySrc started at 06:11:47Z and aborted at 06:12:46Z. Job ended at 06:18:16Z.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_confidence\",\"name\":\"RCA confidence level\",\"description\":\"The RCA states high confidence for the systemic VerifySrc pattern and high confidence that the step was aborted during an outbound transfer, but medium confidence on the specific abort trigger because step logs are required.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_sources_used\",\"name\":\"Sources used in RCA\",\"description\":\"Sources cited include CloudBees job payload, Datadog host inventory, Datadog metrics for network, IO, CPU, and disk, Datadog Artifactory logs, Datadog incidents, and cross-job analysis for jobs f179cb7a and f179cb72.\"}],\"relationships\":[{\"id\":\"rel_procedure_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Procedure extracted from the RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Failed step extracted from the RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_class_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Step class extracted from the RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_class_source_verification\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_procedure_has_step\",\"name\":\"has_step\",\"description\":\"Build.Rel.602829 contained the failed VerifySrc step.\",\"source_id\":\"procedure_build_rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_instance_of_class\",\"name\":\"instance_of\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc is a source verification step.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\",\"target_id\":\"step_class_source_verification\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_job_error_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Job error symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_job_error_aborted\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_exit_code_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Exit code symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_verifysrc_exit_code_2\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_inbound_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Inbound transfer symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_large_inbound_prestep\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_outbound_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Outbound transfer symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_sustained_outbound_transfer\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_abort_transfer_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Abort during outbound transfer symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_abort_during_outbound_transfer\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_cross_job_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Cross-job pattern symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_cross_job_pattern\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_same_host_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Same-host repeat symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_same_host_repeat\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_disk_jump_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Disk jump symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_disk_usage_jump_secondary\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_overlap_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Overlapping execution symptom extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_overlapping_job_execution\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_has_exit_code_symptom\",\"name\":\"has_symptom\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc exhibited exit code 2.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\",\"target_id\":\"symptom_verifysrc_exit_code_2\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_has_abort_transfer_symptom\",\"name\":\"has_symptom\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc aborted during the outbound transfer window.\",\"source_id\":\"step_verifysrc_f179ca58_867f_f12f_be4a_1ea035bf3243\",\"target_id\":\"symptom_abort_during_outbound_transfer\"},{\"id\":\"rel_root_cause_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Probable root cause extracted from the RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_outbound_supports_root_cause\",\"name\":\"supports\",\"description\":\"Sustained outbound transfer supports the probable VerifySrc upload abort root cause.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_sustained_outbound_transfer\",\"target_id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\"},{\"id\":\"rel_abort_supports_root_cause\",\"name\":\"supports\",\"description\":\"Abort during transfer window supports the probable VerifySrc upload abort root cause.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_abort_during_outbound_transfer\",\"target_id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\"},{\"id\":\"rel_cross_job_supports_root_cause\",\"name\":\"supports\",\"description\":\"Recurring cross-job pattern supports the systemic VerifySrc issue root cause.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_cross_job_pattern\",\"target_id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\"},{\"id\":\"rel_same_host_supports_root_cause\",\"name\":\"supports\",\"description\":\"Repeated same-host failure supports persistence of the failure mode.\",\"source_id\":\"symptom_same_host_repeat\",\"target_id\":\"root_cause_systemic_verifysrc_upload_abort\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_agent_metrics_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Agent metrics availability status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_agent_metrics_available\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_no_logs_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"No log pipeline status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_no_datadog_log_pipeline\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_cpu_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"CPU status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_cpu_not_bottleneck\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_io_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"IO status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_io_not_bottleneck\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_disk_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Disk status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_disk_not_cause_for_this_job\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_memory_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Memory status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_no_memory_pressure\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_ldap_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"LDAP status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_no_ldap_failures\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_incidents_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Incident status extracted from source log.\",\"source_id\":\"status_no_active_incidents\",\"target_id\":\"log_rca_179ca58_7a71_f11a_8dc3_4efb9ff91010\"},{\"id\":\"rel_status_commander_extracted\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\