  {
    "file_name": "RCA_f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010.txt",
    "log_text": "CloudBees Job: f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010\nGenerated: 2026-07-07 | Analyst: NOVA (Next-Generation Observability Virtual Agent)\n\n1. Executive Summary\nJob Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1 (Project: CRMBuilds, Procedure: Build.Rel.602829) failed during the VerifySrc step on agent host crm-ubuntulv118 between 06:27:05Z \u2013 06:30:27Z on 2026-07-07. The build outcome was classified as a Compile failure.\n\nThe root cause is a sustained, farm-wide CIFS/SMB authentication failure against the QCDFS shared file server (\\\\qcdfs), confirmed to have been active from at least 06:00:00Z through 07:29:59Z \u2014 a continuous 90-minute outage. A total of 50,676+ CIFS SessSetup = -13 (EACCES) errors were recorded across 19 build hosts during this window, firing at a sustained rate of ~560 errors/minute with no recovery.\n\nA critical secondary finding was discovered: logs from host lpi-aci-ubld040 explicitly confirm the root mechanism \u2014 Kerberos key expiry: [Errno 127] Key has expired: '/mnt/qcdfs/...'. This confirms the CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors are caused by expired Kerberos credentials on the build farm hosts, preventing QCDFS mount authentication.\n\nThe VerifySrc step on crm-ubuntulv118 \u2014 which requires reading source files from QCDFS-mounted shares \u2014 could not authenticate to the file server due to this expired Kerberos ticket, causing source verification to fail and the build to report a Compile failure. Agent host crm-ubuntulv118 has no Datadog telemetry coverage, but the failure mode is consistent with and confirmed by the farm-wide Kerberos expiry evidence.\n\nThis is the same root cause as job f179cd8b (Aurora.LA.3.1-00150-STD.PROD-2), confirming a systemic QCDFS Kerberos outage affecting the entire CRMBuilds farm during this window.\n\n2. Job Context\nJob ID: f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010\nJob Name: Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1_20260706_232502_232522\nProject: CRMBuilds\nProcedure: Build.Rel.602829\nOutcome: completed_error / error\nFailed Step: VerifySrc\nFailed Reason (Build): Compile\nAgent Host: crm-ubuntulv118\nStep Exit Code: 0 (process exited cleanly \u2014 failure detected by step verification logic, not an OS crash)\nStep Duration: ~201 seconds (06:27:05Z \u2013 06:30:27Z)\n3. Build Timeline\nTime (UTC)\tEvent\tSource\n06:00:00Z\tQCDFS CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors begin \u2014 556 errors in first minute\tDatadog Logs (aci_syslog)\n06:00:00Z \u2013 06:25:00Z\tSustained CIFS errors at ~560/min across 19 build hosts \u2014 Kerberos tickets expired farm-wide\tDatadog Logs (aci_syslog)\n06:25:22Z\tCloudBees Job f179cca2 starts on crm-ubuntulv118\tCloudBees Metadata\n06:27:05Z\tVerifySrc step begins \u2014 attempts to access QCDFS-mounted source paths\tCloudBees Metadata\n06:27:00Z \u2013 06:30:27Z\tQCDFS CIFS errors actively firing during entire VerifySrc step \u2014 564\u2013570 errors/min confirmed\tDatadog Logs (per-minute analysis)\n06:30:27Z\tVerifySrc step ends \u2014 FAILED (exit code 0, source verification failed)\tCloudBees Metadata\n06:33:42Z\tJob ends with status: completed_error\tCloudBees Metadata\n07:29:59Z\tLast recorded CIFS error in telemetry window \u2014 outage still active at query boundary\tDatadog Logs (aci_syslog)\n4. Execution Path Inventory\nFailed Step: VerifySrc (stepId: f179cca2-24b5-f148-8b4a-4efb9ff91010)\nAgent Host: crm-ubuntulv118 \u2014 \u26a0\ufe0f No Datadog telemetry coverage (not registered in Datadog infrastructure)\nCommander Host: Not identified \u2014 no evidence of Commander contribution to failure\nInvoked File Service: \\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com \u2014 CIFS/SMB shared file server hosting CRMBuilds source files (mount path: /mnt/qcdfs/...)\nAuthentication Service: Kerberos KDC \u2014 expired tickets confirmed as the mechanism behind CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors\n5. Detected Error Codes\n\ud83d\udd34 Primary: CIFS VFS SessSetup = -13 (EACCES)\nError Code: -13 = EACCES \u2014 Permission Denied / Authentication Failure\nProtocol: SMB/CIFS \u2014 Session Setup phase (authentication handshake)\nTarget Server: \\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com\nFirst Occurrence: 2026-07-07T06:00:00Z (earliest in query window)\nLast Occurrence: 2026-07-07T07:29:59Z\nTotal Count: 50,676+ log entries\nRate: ~560 errors/minute \u2014 sustained, no recovery observed\nAffected Hosts: 19 confirmed (fra-aci-ubld225\u2013430, lpi-aci-ubld005/006/040/045/148, fra-aci-ubld203/412)\nEvidence Source: Datadog Logs (flex tier), service: aci_syslog\n\ud83d\udd34 Root Mechanism Confirmed: Kerberos Key Expiry\nError: [Errno 127] Key has expired: '/mnt/qcdfs/adas/SE03/DataLake/DCS02'\nSource Host: lpi-aci-ubld040\nTimestamp: 2026-07-07T06:34:58Z\nProcess: ansible-ansible.builtin.find \u2014 attempting to access QCDFS mount\nSignificance: This log entry directly confirms that the CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors are caused by expired Kerberos tickets on build farm hosts. The CIFS client cannot re-authenticate to QCDFS because the Kerberos credential (keytab/TGT) has expired.\nEvidence Source: Datadog Logs (flex tier), service: aci_syslog\nStep Exit Code: 0\nThe VerifySrc step process exited with code 0 \u2014 no OS-level crash. The failure was detected by the step's own verification logic, consistent with a \"source files not accessible\" condition rather than a compiler crash.\n6. Correlated Observations\nCloudBees\nJob f179cca2 failed at VerifySrc step with exit code 0 and build outcome \"Compile\".\nStep duration was ~201 seconds (06:27:05 \u2013 06:30:27Z), suggesting the step ran its full verification cycle but found source files inaccessible.\nThis is the second confirmed job failure with identical characteristics in the same time window (cf. job f179cd8b \u2014 Aurora build, same procedure, same step, same exit code).\nNo other jobs on crm-ubuntulv118 could be identified due to absence of telemetry on that host.\nAgent Host (crm-ubuntulv118)\n\u26a0\ufe0f Agent host crm-ubuntulv118 has no Datadog telemetry coverage.\nThe host is not registered in the Datadog infrastructure inventory. No CPU, memory, disk, network metrics, or logs are available from this host. Root cause cannot be confirmed from direct monitoring data for this specific host. CloudBees step execution logs from crm-ubuntulv118 must be examined directly for definitive confirmation.\n\nCommander Host\nNo evidence of Commander-side failure. Commander is not implicated in this failure.\nDatadog \u2014 QCDFS / Kerberos (Key Finding)\n50,676+ CIFS SessSetup = -13 (EACCES) errors recorded against \\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com between 06:00Z and 07:30Z.\nErrors were active at a constant rate of ~560/min during the entire VerifySrc step window (06:27:05 \u2013 06:30:27Z):\n06:27:00Z \u2192 564 errors\n06:28:00Z \u2192 566 errors\n06:29:00Z \u2192 566 errors\n06:30:00Z \u2192 570 errors\nKerberos key expiry explicitly confirmed on host lpi-aci-ubld040 at 06:34:58Z: [Errno 127] Key has expired: '/mnt/qcdfs/...'\nErrors began at least 27 minutes before the job started (06:00Z vs job start 06:25Z) \u2014 the outage was pre-existing.\n19 distinct build hosts affected simultaneously \u2014 confirms server-side or farm-wide credential issue, not a per-host problem.\nTop affected hosts by error count: fra-aci-ubld429 (4,816), fra-aci-ubld229 (4,816), fra-aci-ubld228 (4,810).\nService owner: arriverci.admins (ops: fabian_stiegler, dev: hans_hazelius, solution: lars_erik_rosengren).\nNo formal Datadog incident was declared for this outage.\nSplunk\nSplunk was not queried \u2014 Datadog flex logs provided sufficient and conclusive evidence for this investigation.\nExternal Dependency\nQCDFS.qualcomm.com \u2014 CIFS/SMB file server. Kerberos authentication failures (EACCES + key expiry) are the confirmed root mechanism. The QCDFS mount at /mnt/qcdfs/ was inaccessible to all build farm hosts during the outage window.\nKerberos KDC \u2014 The Kerberos ticket-granting infrastructure is implicated. Either the TGT/service tickets expired and were not renewed, or the KDC was unreachable for renewal.\n7. Probable Root Cause\nFarm-Wide Kerberos Ticket Expiry Causing QCDFS CIFS Authentication Failure\n\nThe VerifySrc step on agent crm-ubuntulv118 failed because the build agent could not authenticate to the \\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com CIFS/SMB file server to access source files required for source verification. The Linux kernel CIFS client returned error -13 (EACCES) during the SMB session setup phase.\n\nThe root mechanism is confirmed as Kerberos key expiry \u2014 explicitly logged on host lpi-aci-ubld040 as [Errno 127] Key has expired: '/mnt/qcdfs/...'. When Kerberos tickets expire, the CIFS client cannot complete the SMB session setup authentication handshake, resulting in EACCES. This affected all 19 monitored build farm hosts simultaneously, indicating either:\n\nA farm-wide Kerberos keytab/TGT expiry (all hosts share the same credential lifecycle), or\nThe Kerberos KDC became unreachable, preventing ticket renewal across the farm\nSupporting evidence:\n\n\u2705 Explicit [Errno 127] Key has expired log on QCDFS mount path at 06:34:58Z\n\u2705 50,676+ CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors across 19 hosts \u2014 sustained 90+ minute outage\n\u2705 Errors active at constant ~560/min rate during the entire VerifySrc step window\n\u2705 Outage pre-existed the job start by 27+ minutes \u2014 not triggered by this job\n\u2705 Simultaneous failure across all build farm hosts \u2014 rules out per-host issue\n\u2705 Step exit code 0 \u2014 consistent with \"source not found/accessible\" rather than compiler crash\n\u2705 Build failure reason \"Compile\" \u2014 downstream classification from inaccessible source files\n\u2705 Identical failure pattern to job f179cd8b in the same window \u2014 confirms systemic cause\n8. Confidence Level\nMEDIUM-HIGH\n\nReason:\n\nRaises to MEDIUM-HIGH (vs. MEDIUM for the Aurora job) because the Kerberos key expiry mechanism is explicitly confirmed in logs ([Errno 127] Key has expired), not just inferred from EACCES codes.\nCapped below HIGH because:\nAgent host crm-ubuntulv118 has no direct Datadog telemetry \u2014 the Kerberos expiry was not observed on this specific host\nThe Kerberos expiry was confirmed on lpi-aci-ubld040 (Link\u00f6ping, Sweden) \u2014 a different site/pool than crm-ubuntulv118\nCloudBees step execution logs from crm-ubuntulv118 were not accessible for direct confirmation\n9. Infrastructure vs Code Assessment\nInfrastructure Issue: YES\nCode Issue: NO\nMixed: NO\nReason: The failure is entirely attributable to a shared infrastructure component \u2014 the QCDFS file server's Kerberos authentication layer. Expired Kerberos tickets prevented CIFS session setup across the entire build farm. No compiler errors, syntax errors, missing symbols, or code-level failures were identified. The \"Compile\" failure reason in the build metadata is a downstream classification resulting from inaccessible source files, not a code defect. The same infrastructure failure caused at least two confirmed job failures (Kobuk and Aurora builds) in the same time window.\n\n10. Recommended Remediation\nImmediate: Renew Kerberos credentials on all build farm hosts\nRun kinit or klist -e on all fra-aci-ubld*, lpi-aci-ubld*, and crm-ubuntu* / crm-ubuntulv* hosts to check ticket status and renew expired TGTs. Contact arriverci.admins (fabian_stiegler) to coordinate farm-wide credential renewal.\nVerify QCDFS mount accessibility\nAfter credential renewal, verify on representative hosts: ls /mnt/qcdfs/ and mount | grep qcdfs. Confirm CIFS SessSetup errors cease in Datadog logs.\nRe-run both failed jobs\nOnce QCDFS access is confirmed restored, re-trigger:\nJob f179cca2 \u2014 Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1\nJob f179cd8b \u2014 Aurora.LA.3.1-00150-STD.PROD-2\nAudit all other CRMBuilds jobs in the 06:00\u201307:30Z window\nIdentify all jobs that ran during the QCDFS outage window and re-trigger any that failed with \"Compile\" / VerifySrc failures.\nInstall Datadog agent on crm-ubuntulv118 and crm-ubuntu359\nBoth agent hosts have zero telemetry coverage. Install the Datadog agent to enable CPU, memory, disk, network, and log collection for future investigations.\n11. Preventive Actions\nAutomated Kerberos ticket renewal\nImplement k5start, msktutil, or a systemd timer to automatically renew Kerberos TGTs on all build farm hosts before expiry. Set renewal threshold at 80% of ticket lifetime.\nQCDFS mount health monitor\nCreate a Datadog monitor: alert when CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors exceed 50 occurrences within 5 minutes across any build host. Route to arriverci.admins PagerDuty.\nKerberos ticket expiry monitor\nCreate a Datadog log monitor for [Errno 127] Key has expired on QCDFS mount paths. Alert immediately on first occurrence \u2014 this is a leading indicator of the CIFS failure cascade.\nPre-flight QCDFS connectivity check in VerifySrc\nAdd a CloudBees pre-step that validates QCDFS mount accessibility and Kerberos ticket validity before starting VerifySrc. Fail fast with a clear, actionable error message (e.g., \"QCDFS mount unavailable \u2014 Kerberos ticket expired\") rather than a generic \"Compile\" failure.\nFormal incident declaration for farm-wide outages\nThe QCDFS Kerberos outage (50,676+ errors, 19 hosts, 90+ minutes, 2+ confirmed job failures) was not declared as a formal incident. Implement auto-incident creation triggered by the CIFS error monitor above.\nDatadog agent deployment across all CRMBuilds agents\nEnsure all CloudBees build agents (including crm-ubuntulv* and crm-ubuntu* pools) have Datadog agents installed and reporting to enable future RCA investigations.\n12. Sources Used\nSource Type\tQuery Window\tEvidence\tConfidence\nDatadog Logs (flex)\t06:00Z \u2013 07:30Z\t50,676+ CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors on 19 build hosts targeting \\\\QCDFS; Kerberos key expiry explicitly confirmed on lpi-aci-ubld040\tHIGH\nDatadog Logs \u2014 Per-Minute Analysis (flex)\t06:00Z \u2013 07:30Z\t90-minute per-minute breakdown confirming ~560 errors/min sustained rate; errors confirmed active during entire VerifySrc step window (06:27\u201306:30Z)\tHIGH\nDatadog Logs \u2014 Step Window Analysis (flex)\t06:27Z \u2013 06:31Z\t13 hosts with 2\u2013216 CIFS errors during VerifySrc step window; confirms outage was active during step execution\tHIGH\nDatadog Infrastructure\tCurrent\tcrm-ubuntulv118 not registered in Datadog host inventory \u2014 no telemetry available\tN/A\nDatadog Incidents\t05:00Z \u2013 08:00Z\tNo incidents declared for QCDFS, Kerberos, or CRM during outage window\tN/A\nCloudBees Metadata\tJob payload\tJob ID, step name, exit code 0, agent host crm-ubuntulv118, timestamps, failure reason \"Compile\"\tHIGH\nCross-Job Correlation\t06:25Z \u2013 06:40Z\tJob f179cd8b (Aurora build, same procedure, same step, same exit code) failed in same window \u2014 confirms systemic cause\tHIGH",
    "log_json": "{\"log_record\":{\"id\":\"log_RCA_f179cca2\",\"name\":\"RCA_f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010.txt\",\"description\":\"RCA log for CloudBees Job f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010, generated 2026-07-07 by NOVA. Covers failure of Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1 in CRMBuilds procedure Build.Rel.602829 during VerifySrc.\"},\"procedures\":[{\"id\":\"procedure_Build_Rel_602829\",\"name\":\"Build.Rel.602829\",\"description\":\"CloudBees procedure for project CRMBuilds. Job Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1_20260706_232502_232522 failed while running this procedure.\"}],\"steps\":[{\"id\":\"step_f179cca2_24b5_f148_8b4a_4efb9ff91010\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Failed CloudBees step. Ran on agent host crm-ubuntulv118 from approximately 2026-07-07T06:27:05Z to 2026-07-07T06:30:27Z. Step exit code was 0, but source verification failed and the build was classified as Compile failure.\"}],\"step_classes\":[{\"id\":\"step_class_VerifySrc\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc source verification\",\"description\":\"Step class requiring access to source files on QCDFS-mounted paths such as /mnt/qcdfs/... . Failure mode in this RCA is source verification failure when QCDFS source paths are inaccessible.\"}],\"log_symptoms\":[{\"id\":\"symptom_build_completed_error_compile\",\"name\":\"CloudBees job completed_error with Compile classification\",\"description\":\"Job f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010 ended at 2026-07-07T06:33:42Z with status completed_error / error and failed reason Compile.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_VerifySrc_failed_exit_0\",\"name\":\"VerifySrc failed despite exit code 0\",\"description\":\"VerifySrc process exited cleanly with code 0, indicating the failure was detected by step verification logic rather than an OS-level crash.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_CIFS_SessSetup_EACCES\",\"name\":\"CIFS VFS SessSetup = -13 EACCES errors\",\"description\":\"Datadog logs recorded 50,676+ CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors targeting \\\\\\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com from at least 2026-07-07T06:00:00Z through 2026-07-07T07:29:59Z across 19 build hosts, at approximately 560 errors per minute.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_Kerberos_key_expired\",\"name\":\"Kerberos key expired on QCDFS mount\",\"description\":\"Datadog log on host lpi-aci-ubld040 at 2026-07-07T06:34:58Z reported [Errno 127] Key has expired: '/mnt/qcdfs/adas/SE03/DataLake/DCS02' while ansible-ansible.builtin.find attempted to access the QCDFS mount.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_QCDFS_errors_during_VerifySrc\",\"name\":\"QCDFS authentication errors active during VerifySrc window\",\"description\":\"During the VerifySrc window, Datadog per-minute analysis showed CIFS errors continuing: 564 at 06:27Z, 566 at 06:28Z, 566 at 06:29Z, and 570 at 06:30Z.\"},{\"id\":\"symptom_cross_job_same_pattern\",\"name\":\"Second job failed with identical pattern\",\"description\":\"RCA states that job f179cd8b, Aurora.LA.3.1-00150-STD.PROD-2, failed in the same window with the same procedure, same step, and same exit code, supporting a systemic failure pattern.\"}],\"system_statuses\":[{\"id\":\"status_QCDFS_Kerberos_outage\",\"name\":\"QCDFS Kerberos authentication outage active\",\"description\":\"QCDFS CIFS/SMB authentication failure was active from at least 2026-07-07T06:00:00Z to 2026-07-07T07:29:59Z, with no recovery observed within the telemetry window.\"},{\"id\":\"status_farm_wide_impact\",\"name\":\"Farm-wide impact across monitored build hosts\",\"description\":\"CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors were observed across 19 confirmed build hosts, indicating a farm-wide or shared infrastructure issue rather than an isolated per-host failure.\"},{\"id\":\"status_infrastructure_issue\",\"name\":\"Infrastructure issue, not code issue\",\"description\":\"RCA classifies the failure as Infrastructure Issue: YES, Code Issue: NO, Mixed: NO. No compiler errors, syntax errors, missing symbols, or code-level failures were identified.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_commander_failure_evidence\",\"name\":\"No Commander-side failure evidence\",\"description\":\"RCA states there was no evidence of Commander-side failure and Commander was not implicated.\"},{\"id\":\"status_no_formal_incident\",\"name\":\"No formal Datadog incident declared\",\"description\":\"Datadog Incidents query for 05:00Z\u201308:00Z found no incidents declared for QCDFS, Kerberos, or CRM during the outage window.\"}],\"root_causes\":[{\"id\":\"root_cause_farm_wide_Kerberos_ticket_expiry_QCDFS_auth_failure\",\"name\":\"Farm-wide Kerberos ticket expiry causing QCDFS CIFS authentication failure\",\"description\":\"The VerifySrc step failed because the build agent could not authenticate to \\\\\\\\QCDFS.qualcomm.com over CIFS/SMB to access source files. Linux CIFS returned -13 EACCES during SMB session setup. The mechanism is supported by explicit [Errno 127] Key has expired evidence on a QCDFS mount and by sustained farm-wide CIFS SessSetup errors.\"}],\"data_gaps\":[{\"id\":\"gap_no_datadog_telemetry_crm_ubuntulv118\",\"name\":\"No Datadog telemetry for crm-ubuntulv118\",\"description\":\"Agent host crm-ubuntulv118 was not registered in Datadog infrastructure inventory. No CPU, memory, disk, network metrics, or logs were available from this specific host.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_no_direct_kerberos_expiry_on_crm_ubuntulv118\",\"name\":\"Kerberos expiry not directly observed on failing agent\",\"description\":\"The explicit [Errno 127] Key has expired log was observed on lpi-aci-ubld040, not on crm-ubuntulv118. RCA infers consistency for crm-ubuntulv118 from farm-wide evidence and timing.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_cloudbees_step_logs_unavailable\",\"name\":\"CloudBees step execution logs from crm-ubuntulv118 unavailable\",\"description\":\"RCA states CloudBees step execution logs from crm-ubuntulv118 must be examined directly for definitive confirmation, but they were not available in the investigation.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_commander_host_not_identified\",\"name\":\"Commander host not identified\",\"description\":\"Execution path inventory states the Commander host was not identified, though there was no evidence of Commander contribution to the failure.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_exact_kerberos_failure_mode_unresolved\",\"name\":\"Exact Kerberos renewal failure mode unresolved\",\"description\":\"RCA identifies either farm-wide Kerberos keytab/TGT expiry or KDC unreachability preventing renewal as possible underlying mechanisms; the exact one is not proven.\"},{\"id\":\"gap_splunk_not_queried\",\"name\":\"Splunk not queried\",\"description\":\"RCA states Splunk was not queried because Datadog flex logs were considered sufficient and conclusive for this investigation.\"}],\"preventive_actions\":[{\"id\":\"preventive_automated_kerberos_ticket_renewal\",\"name\":\"Automated Kerberos ticket renewal\",\"description\":\"Implement k5start, msktutil, or a systemd timer to automatically renew Kerberos TGTs on all build farm hosts before expiry, with renewal threshold at 80% of ticket lifetime.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_QCDFS_mount_health_monitor\",\"name\":\"QCDFS mount health monitor\",\"description\":\"Create a Datadog monitor alerting when CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors exceed 50 occurrences within 5 minutes across any build host, routed to arriverci.admins PagerDuty.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_Kerberos_key_expiry_monitor\",\"name\":\"Kerberos ticket expiry monitor\",\"description\":\"Create a Datadog log monitor for [Errno 127] Key has expired on QCDFS mount paths and alert immediately on first occurrence.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_VerifySrc_preflight_QCDFS_check\",\"name\":\"Pre-flight QCDFS connectivity check in VerifySrc\",\"description\":\"Add a CloudBees pre-step validating QCDFS mount accessibility and Kerberos ticket validity before VerifySrc, failing fast with a clear error such as QCDFS mount unavailable \u2014 Kerberos ticket expired.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_auto_incident_for_farm_outages\",\"name\":\"Formal incident declaration for farm-wide outages\",\"description\":\"Implement auto-incident creation triggered by the CIFS error monitor for farm-wide QCDFS Kerberos outages.\"},{\"id\":\"preventive_Datadog_agents_all_CRMBuilds_agents\",\"name\":\"Datadog agent deployment across all CRMBuilds agents\",\"description\":\"Ensure all CloudBees build agents, including crm-ubuntulv* and crm-ubuntu* pools, have Datadog agents installed and reporting for future RCA investigations.\"}],\"remediations\":[{\"id\":\"remediation_renew_kerberos_credentials\",\"name\":\"Renew Kerberos credentials on all build farm hosts\",\"description\":\"Run kinit or klist -e on all fra-aci-ubld*, lpi-aci-ubld*, and crm-ubuntu* / crm-ubuntulv* hosts to check ticket status and renew expired TGTs. Coordinate with arriverci.admins / fabian_stiegler.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_verify_QCDFS_mount_accessibility\",\"name\":\"Verify QCDFS mount accessibility\",\"description\":\"After credential renewal, verify on representative hosts with ls /mnt/qcdfs/ and mount | grep qcdfs, and confirm CIFS SessSetup errors cease in Datadog logs.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_rerun_failed_jobs\",\"name\":\"Re-run failed jobs\",\"description\":\"After QCDFS access is restored, re-trigger job f179cca2 \u2014 Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1 \u2014 and job f179cd8b \u2014 Aurora.LA.3.1-00150-STD.PROD-2.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_audit_jobs_during_outage\",\"name\":\"Audit CRMBuilds jobs during outage window\",\"description\":\"Identify all CRMBuilds jobs that ran during the 06:00Z\u201307:30Z QCDFS outage window and re-trigger any that failed with Compile or VerifySrc failures.\"},{\"id\":\"remediation_install_datadog_agent_missing_hosts\",\"name\":\"Install Datadog agent on uncovered hosts\",\"description\":\"Install Datadog agent on crm-ubuntulv118 and crm-ubuntu359, both reported as having zero telemetry coverage.\"}],\"annotations\":[{\"id\":\"annotation_confidence_medium_high\",\"name\":\"Confidence level MEDIUM-HIGH\",\"description\":\"Confidence was raised because Kerberos key expiry was explicitly confirmed in logs, but capped below HIGH because crm-ubuntulv118 had no direct Datadog telemetry, the key expiry was observed on lpi-aci-ubld040, and CloudBees step logs from crm-ubuntulv118 were unavailable.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_job_context\",\"name\":\"Job context\",\"description\":\"Job ID f179cca2-18f5-f1a4-9b68-4efb9ff91010; job name Kobuk.LE.3.1-00093-EBOOT.CPE.WKK-1_20260706_232502_232522; project CRMBuilds; procedure Build.Rel.602829; agent host crm-ubuntulv118; job started 06:25:22Z and ended 06:33:42Z.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_datadog_sources\",\"name\":\"Datadog evidence sources\",\"description\":\"Datadog flex logs, per-minute analysis, and step-window analysis showed sustained CIFS SessSetup = -13 errors, active during VerifySrc, with explicit Kerberos key expiry on lpi-aci-ubld040.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_cloudbees_metadata_source\",\"name\":\"CloudBees metadata evidence\",\"description\":\"CloudBees metadata provided job ID, step name, exit code 0, agent host crm-ubuntulv118, timestamps, and failure reason Compile.\"},{\"id\":\"annotation_service_owner\",\"name\":\"Service owner noted in RCA\",\"description\":\"RCA lists service owner arriverci.admins with ops contact fabian_stiegler, dev contact hans_hazelius, and solution contact lars_erik_rosengren.\"}],\"relationships\":[{\"id\":\"rel_proc_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Procedure extracted from RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"procedure_Build_Rel_602829\",\"target_id\":\"log_RCA_f179cca2\"},{\"id\":\"rel_step_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Failed step extracted from RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_f179cca2_24b5_f148_8b4a_4efb9ff91010\",\"target_id\":\"log_RCA_f179cca2\"},{\"id\":\"rel_stepclass_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\",\"description\":\"Step class extracted from RCA source log.\",\"source_id\":\"step_class_VerifySrc\",\"target_id\":\"log_RCA_f179cca2\"},{\"id\":\"rel_symptom_build_extracted_from_log\",\"name\":\"extracted_from\"